{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784444172245,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Duoy0vS3HsN7J1kn3GfTzvrf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/.executor-state"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/.executor-state</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n\n\n(0 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/.executor-state","entries":[],"offset":1,"totalEntries":0,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/.executor-state","time":{"start":1784444172234,"end":1784444172235}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08341c15d884b8b1016a5c750c1c808191afe81aef66cf66c4"}},"id":"prt_f792937c9001tWa3uiEPeeQZcz","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f7929132c001D9endXAwYI5Bt4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784444172245,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8wEdT46tQgTicMVoi2de7NZM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n3: description: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"research findings registry\"\n7:   - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n8:   - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n9:   - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n10:   - \"research dashboard derivation\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.2\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n17: \n18: The reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n39: \n40: The workflow reducer:\n41: \n42: - reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n43: - reads `inbox.jsonl` as immutable question input;\n44: - reads the prior registry as canonical question state when present;\n45: - validates required iteration artifacts;\n46: - updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n47: - regenerates the findings registry;\n48: - regenerates the dashboard;\n49: - records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n50: \n51: It must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n56: \n57: The canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n58: \n59: ```json\n60: {\n61:   \"openQuestions\": [],\n62:   \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n63:   \"keyFindings\": [],\n64:   \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n65:   \"coverageBySources\": {},\n66:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n67:   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n68:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n69:   \"graphDecision\": null,\n70:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n71:   \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: Question ownership:\n76: \n77: - `inbox.jsonl` is append-only input for external questions.\n78: - The registry is the canonical owner of promoted question text, provenance, and operator decisions.\n79: - The strategy `key-questions` block is a generated projection and is rewritten from registry state on every reduce step.\n80: \n81: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question by promoted question id or inbox id but carries different text, the reducer records a conflict instead of overwriting markdown. Conflict records use `operatorDecision` values of `accepted`, `rejected`, `superseded`, or `needs_decision`; the default unresolved decision is `needs_decision`. The emitted `question_conflict` JSONL event includes both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n82: \n83: The reducer writes the registry to `findings-registry.json`; this is the canonical live name. `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is a legacy read-fallback path only -- the reducer checks it when `findings-registry.json` is absent but never writes to it. New docs should reference `findings-registry.json` and mention the legacy name only when explaining read-compatibility.\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n88: \n89: Blocking validation:\n90: \n91: - config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n92: - every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n93: - every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n94: - JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n95: - reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n96: - convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n97: \n98: Post-dispatch failure codes include:\n99: \n100: | Code | Meaning |\n101: |------|---------|\n102: | `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n103: | `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n104: | `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n105: | `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n106: | `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n107: \n108: Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n113: \n114: Fault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n115: \n116: Safe recovery order:\n117: \n118: 1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n119: 2. Read valid JSONL records.\n120: 3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n121: 4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n122: 5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n123: 6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n124: \n125: Example reconstructed record:\n126: \n127: ```json\n128: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n134: \n135: The config may include:\n136: \n137: ```json\n138: {\n139:   \"fileProtection\": {\n140:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n141:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n142:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n143:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n144:     \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n145:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n146:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n147:   }\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: Protection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n156: \n157: Dashboard values are derived from raw state:\n158: \n159: | Dashboard Field | Source |\n160: |-----------------|--------|\n161: | iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n162: | current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n163: | convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n164: | blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n165: | graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n166: | next focus | strategy |\n167: \n168: `synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n173: \n174: The workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.\n\n(End of file - total 174 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\ndescription: Reducer ownership, findings registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, and reconstruction rules.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research reducer registry\"\n  - \"research findings registry\"\n  - \"reducer ownership contract\"\n  - \"research registry fingerprint\"\n  - \"reducer fault tolerance\"\n  - \"research dashboard derivation\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.2\n---\n\n# Deep Research Reducer And Registry Reference\n\nThe reducer turns append-only iteration state into synchronized strategy, registry, dashboard, and synthesis metadata. It is the source of truth for derived packet state.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine reducer ownership, findings registry shape, validation behavior, fault tolerance, file protection, dashboard derivation, and legacy aliases.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when rebuilding derived state, validating registry/dashboard outputs, or deciding whether a file is agent-owned or reducer-owned.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe reducer owns derived state. Manual edits to reducer-managed outputs are temporary and may be overwritten.\n\n---\n\n## 2. REDUCER CONTRACT\n\nThe workflow reducer:\n\n- reads `deep-research-state.jsonl`, per-iteration deltas, strategy, and iteration markdown;\n- reads `inbox.jsonl` as immutable question input;\n- reads the prior registry as canonical question state when present;\n- validates required iteration artifacts;\n- updates machine-owned strategy sections;\n- regenerates the findings registry;\n- regenerates the dashboard;\n- records convergence and blocked-stop summaries.\n\nIt must fail closed before writing derived files when JSONL corruption is detected in strict mode.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe canonical registry stores open/resolved questions, findings, ruled-out directions, convergence state, and blocked-stop history.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"openQuestions\": [],\n  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n  \"keyFindings\": [],\n  \"ruledOutDirections\": [],\n  \"coverageBySources\": {},\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.42,\n  \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": null,\n  \"graphDecision\": null,\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nQuestion ownership:\n\n- `inbox.jsonl` is append-only input for external questions.\n- The registry is the canonical owner of promoted question text, provenance, and operator decisions.\n- The strategy `key-questions` block is a generated projection and is rewritten from registry state on every reduce step.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question by promoted question id or inbox id but carries different text, the reducer records a conflict instead of overwriting markdown. Conflict records use `operatorDecision` values of `accepted`, `rejected`, `superseded`, or `needs_decision`; the default unresolved decision is `needs_decision`. The emitted `question_conflict` JSONL event includes both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\nThe reducer writes the registry to `findings-registry.json`; this is the canonical live name. `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is a legacy read-fallback path only -- the reducer checks it when `findings-registry.json` is absent but never writes to it. New docs should reference `findings-registry.json` and mention the legacy name only when explaining read-compatibility.\n\n---\n\n## 4. VALIDATION RULES\n\nBlocking validation:\n\n- config, state log, and strategy exist before a resume;\n- every dispatched iteration produces a non-empty iteration markdown file;\n- every dispatched iteration appends a JSONL delta record with required fields;\n- JSONL records parse in strict mode;\n- reducer-owned outputs refresh after iteration evaluation;\n- convergence STOP candidates record gate evidence.\n\nPost-dispatch failure codes include:\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `iteration_file_missing` | Expected iteration markdown file was not created |\n| `iteration_file_empty` | Iteration markdown exists but is empty |\n| `jsonl_not_appended` | JSONL state did not receive the iteration record |\n| `jsonl_missing_fields` | Required JSONL fields are absent |\n| `jsonl_parse_error` | JSONL line is malformed |\n\nThree consecutive failures route to stuck recovery or escalation.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FAULT TOLERANCE\n\nFault-tolerant reads may skip malformed JSONL lines only in lenient recovery mode. Strict mode stops before derived writes.\n\nSafe recovery order:\n\n1. Preserve the corrupted state file.\n2. Read valid JSONL records.\n3. Reconstruct missing iteration summaries from `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n4. Append explicit reconstructed records.\n5. Regenerate registry and dashboard.\n6. Record the recovery in JSONL.\n\nExample reconstructed record:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"status\":\"reconstructed\",\"focus\":\"extracted focus\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. FILE PROTECTION MAP\n\nThe config may include:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nProtection is a workflow contract. It documents ownership and supports validation; it is not a substitute for command-level checks.\n\n---\n\n## 7. DASHBOARD DERIVATION\n\nDashboard values are derived from raw state:\n\n| Dashboard Field | Source |\n|-----------------|--------|\n| iteration count | JSONL iteration records |\n| current status | latest lifecycle or synthesis event |\n| convergence trend | `convergenceSignals` |\n| blocked stops | registry `blockedStopHistory` |\n| graph convergence | registry graph fields |\n| next focus | strategy |\n\n`synthesis_complete` events are authoritative for terminal status when present.\n\n---\n\n## 8. LEGACY ALIASES\n\nThe workflow may dual-read older names during migration windows, but new writes use canonical `deep-research-*` artifacts. Migration reads should append a migration event that records `legacyPath`, `canonicalPath`, and timestamp.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":174,"totalLines":174,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/state/state-reducer-registry.md","time":{"start":1784444172211,"end":1784444172240}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08341c15d884b8b1016a5c750c1c6881918eedd9fdc5b1815d"}},"id":"prt_f792937ac0011Q16THIpAm2q8Z","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f7929132c001D9endXAwYI5Bt4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784444172246,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_m0Nbsw7gE8W4gBLOWjGbYTGx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: deep-research\n3: description: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\n4: mode: subagent\n5: temperature: 0.1\n6: permission:\n7:   read: allow\n8:   write: allow\n9:   edit: allow\n10:   bash: allow\n11:   grep: allow\n12:   glob: allow\n13:   webfetch: allow\n14:   memory: allow\n15:   code_graph_query: allow\n16:   code_graph_context: allow\n17:   chrome_devtools: deny\n18:   task: deny\n19:   list: allow\n20:   patch: deny\n21:   external_directory: allow\n22: ---\n23: \n24: # The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\n25: \n26: Executes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\n27: \n28: **Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n29: \n30: **Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n31: \n32: **Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n33: \n34: **Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n35: \n36: > **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.\n37: \n38: **HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.\n39: - **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n40: - **State-first**: Read config, state JSONL, and strategy before selecting focus or executing research.\n41: - **Packet scope lock**: Write only within the resolved local-owner research packet and only to allowed iteration outputs.\n42: - **Evidence-bound output**: Never claim completion until the iteration file exists, the JSONL append is verified, and every finding has a cited source or inference marker.\n43: - **No speculative recovery**: Do not infer missing state, create replacement control files, or repair reducer-owned files from inside this agent.\n44: - **Read-budget freshness**: Reuse captured evidence and exact anchors before broad rereads. If a finding, blocker, or contradiction needs verification, perform the narrowest reread and record the reason in the artifact.\n45: - **Status honesty**: Do not convert partial success, unresolved contradiction, or stale evidence into completion language. State the exact remaining uncertainty and the next verification step.\n46: \n47: ## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n48: \n49: **Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n50: \n51: **Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n52: \n53: **NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n54: - `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n55: - `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n56: \n57: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND SCOPE LOCK (HARD BLOCK)\n62: \n63: This agent is LEAF-only.\n64: - NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n65: - NEVER use the Task tool.\n66: - Keep research actions self-contained in this single execution.\n67: - If delegation is needed, document it in findings and recommend it for a future iteration.\n68: \n69: Before any write, enforce the packet scope lock:\n70: - Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.\n71: - Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, one write-once `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` per iteration (the structured delta stream required by the iteration prompt contract), optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n72: - Reducer-owned files (`research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, `research/deep-research-dashboard.md`) are read-only for this agent.\n73: - If any intended write path escapes the resolved packet root, targets a reducer-owned file, or would overwrite an existing iteration file or delta file, STOP and return `Status: error` without writing outside the boundary.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n78: \n79: ### Single Iteration Protocol\n80: \n81: Every iteration follows this sequence:\n82: \n83: ```text\n84: 1. READ STATE ──────> Read config + JSONL + strategy.md\n85: 2. VERIFY BOUNDARY ─> Confirm packet root and allowed write targets\n86: 3. DETERMINE FOCUS ─> Pick focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n87: 4. CLASSIFY EDGES ──> Handle ambiguity, contradictions, missing deps, partial success\n88: 5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n89: 6. WRITE FINDINGS ──> Create research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n90: 7. APPEND STATE ────> Add exactly one canonical iteration record to JSONL\n91: 8. WRITE DELTA ─────> Create research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl with the same canonical record\n92: 9. UPDATE RESEARCH ─> Progressively update research/research.md when enabled\n93: 10. VERIFY OUTPUTS ─> Check narrative, state, delta, citations, and scope\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### Step 1: Read State\n97: \n98: Read the paths provided in dispatch context:\n99: - `research/deep-research-config.json` -- lifecycle mode, budgets, packet boundaries\n100: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` -- iteration history\n101: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md` -- focus, key questions, exhausted approaches\n102: - `research/findings-registry.json` (if exists) -- open/resolved questions and key findings\n103: - `research/research-ideas.md` (if exists) -- deferred tangents\n104: \n105: Extract:\n106: - Current iteration number (count JSONL iteration records + 1)\n107: - Remaining key questions\n108: - Exhausted approaches (DO NOT retry these)\n109: - Recommended next focus\n110: - Lifecycle branch from `config.lineage.lineageMode` (`new`, `resume`, or `restart`; `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred -- see `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`)\n111: \n112: **HARD BLOCK -- Missing or unreadable state**:\n113: - If `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, or `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing, unreadable, or structurally corrupt, do not infer a focus and do not execute research actions.\n114: - Do not create replacement config, state, strategy, dashboard, or registry files.\n115: - Return an iteration completion report with `Status: error`, naming the missing or corrupt state file(s), and stop.\n116: \n117: ### Step 2: Verify Boundary\n118: \n119: Before selecting a focus or writing anything:\n120: 1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n121: 2. Precompute intended write paths for this run:\n122:    - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n123:    - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`\n124:    - `research/research.md` only if progressive synthesis is enabled\n125:    - `idea_observed` JSONL rows only if explicit idea capture is allowed\n126:    - `research/research-ideas.md` only if operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed\n127: 3. Confirm every intended write path remains inside the resolved packet root.\n128: 4. Confirm `iteration-NNN.md` does not already exist.\n129: 5. Confirm no reducer-owned file is scheduled for direct edit.\n130: \n131: If any check fails, STOP with `Status: error`. Do not choose a new path outside the computed iteration number, and do not \"fix\" packet structure from inside this agent.\n132: \n133: ### Step 3: Determine Focus\n134: \n135: Before choosing a focus, read strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\":\n136: - `BLOCKED` categories must not be retried or varied.\n137: - `PRODUCTIVE` categories should be preferred for related questions.\n138: - If the selected focus falls inside a BLOCKED category, choose another.\n139: \n140: Use strategy.md \"Next Focus\". If it is empty or vague, pick the first unchecked \"Key Questions (remaining)\" item; if none remain, investigate the lowest-coverage area.\n141: \n142: If multiple focus candidates are equally plausible:\n143: - Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n144: - If two candidates remain tied after that order, choose the narrower one that can be answered with available evidence in this iteration.\n145: - Record deferred focus candidates in the iteration file's `Ruled Out` or `Recommended Next Focus` section.\n146: \n147: For RECOVERY iterations, use a fundamentally different approach than prior iterations, widen or re-angle the search, and check `research/research-ideas.md` for viable escape paths.\n148: \n149: If useful tangents appear outside the current focus, append `idea_observed` JSONL events only when explicitly allowed and packet-local; otherwise record them in the iteration file's `Recommended Next Focus`. Never emit `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; the reducer owns promotion, ranking, and rejection filtering.\n150: \n151: ### Step 4: Classify Edge Cases\n152: \n153: Before research actions, classify any known edge condition and carry that classification into findings:\n154: \n155: | Condition | Trigger | Required Handling |\n156: |-----------|---------|-------------------|\n157: | Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n158: | Contradictory evidence | Two sources make incompatible claims about the same fact | Preserve both claims with citations, state which one is better supported if evidence allows, and avoid marking the question answered unless resolved |\n159: | Missing dependency | Optional file, tool, source, mirror report, or external URL needed for the ideal path is unavailable | Continue with an alternative in-scope source when possible; if the missing item is required state, report `error`; if evidence is partial, report `timeout` or `stuck` honestly |\n160: | Partial success | Some research actions succeed but others fail before the iteration completes | Write successful findings, document failed actions and recovery attempts, and set status based on the strongest truthful outcome |\n161: \n162: Status selection for edge cases:\n163: - Use `complete` when enough cited evidence answers at least one in-scope question despite minor missing sources.\n164: - Use `insight` when contradiction resolution or synthesis materially improves understanding with low new external evidence.\n165: - Use `timeout` when tool/source failures or budget limits prevent adequate coverage but some evidence was gathered.\n166: - Use `stuck` when ambiguity or missing evidence leaves no productive in-scope path after alternatives are tried.\n167: - Use `error` only for unrecoverable state corruption, missing required control files, or write failures that prevent valid artifacts.\n168: \n169: ### Step 5: Execute Research\n170: \n171: Perform 3-5 focused research actions.\n172: \n173: | Tool | When to Use | Example |\n174: |------|-------------|---------|\n175: | WebFetch | Official docs, API references, known URLs | Fetch MDN docs for an API |\n176: | Grep | Code patterns | Search for implementation examples |\n177: | Glob | File discovery | Find config files or tests |\n178: | Read | Specific file contents | Read implementation details |\n179: | memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n180: | Bash | Bounded data gathering | `wc -l`, `jq` for JSON parsing |\n181: \n182: **Budget**: Target 8-11 total tool calls, hard max 12. Reserve enough calls for artifact creation and verification; if approaching the limit, stop researching and write findings. Do not skip output verification to spend a final call on more research.\n183: \n184: **Citation rule**: Every finding must cite a source:\n185: - `[SOURCE: https://url]` for web sources\n186: - `[SOURCE: path/to/file:line]` for codebase sources\n187: - `[SOURCE: memory:spec-folder]` for memory hits\n188: - `[INFERENCE: based on X and Y]` for derived conclusions\n189: \n190: **Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n191: \n192: For source failures, apply Tier 1-2 recovery:\n193: - **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n194: - **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, recommend the focus for \"Exhausted Approaches\" in the iteration file; do not edit strategy directly.\n195: - **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, write the failure in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n196: \n197: ### Step 6: Write Findings\n198: \n199: Create `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`:\n200: \n201: ```markdown\n202: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n203: \n204: ## Focus\n205: [What this iteration investigated and why. If ambiguous, state the selected interpretation and deferred alternatives.]\n206: \n207: ## Findings\n208: 1. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n209: 2. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n210: 3. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n211: \n212: ## Ruled Out\n213: [Approaches tried this iteration that did not yield results, with why they failed.]\n214: \n215: ## Dead Ends\n216: [Paths definitively eliminated and candidates for reducer promotion to strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\".]\n217: \n218: ## Edge Cases\n219: - Ambiguous input: [none or selected interpretation + deferred alternatives]\n220: - Contradictory evidence: [none or source-backed conflict + resolution status]\n221: - Missing dependencies: [none or missing item + fallback used]\n222: - Partial success: [none or successful/failed actions + chosen status rationale]\n223: \n224: ## Sources Consulted\n225: - [URL or file:line reference]\n226: - [URL or file:line reference]\n227: \n228: ## Assessment\n229: - New information ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n230: - Questions addressed: [list]\n231: - Questions answered: [list]\n232: \n233: ## Reflection\n234: - What worked and why: [approach + causal explanation]\n235: - What did not work and why: [failure + root cause]\n236: - What I would do differently: [specific next adjustment]\n237: \n238: ## Recommended Next Focus\n239: [What to investigate next, based on gaps discovered]\n240: ```\n241: \n242: Do not write a placeholder iteration file. If findings are sparse because a tool failed, write the failure and recovery attempts with citations to tool outputs, consulted source paths, or prior packet evidence.\n243: \n244: ### Step 7: Respect Reducer-Owned State\n245: \n246: Do not use `research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, or `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` as primary write targets. Instead:\n247: 1. Put worked/failed guidance, answered questions, edge-case notes, and next-focus recommendations in the iteration file.\n248: 2. Append the structured JSONL record.\n249: 3. Let the workflow reducer refresh strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard.\n250: \n251: ### Step 8: Append State\n252: \n253: Append exactly ONE iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`:\n254: \n255: ```json\n256: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":N,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":N,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"[focus area]\",\"findingsCount\":N,\"newInfoRatio\":0.XX,\"noveltyJustification\":\"1-sentence explanation of newInfoRatio\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"q1\",\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q1\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"approach1\",\"approach2\"],\"focusTrack\":\"optional-track-label\",\"edgeCase\":\"none\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"WebFetch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"https://example.com/doc\",\"src/file.ts:42\"],\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"durationMs\":NNNNN,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n257: ```\n258: \n259: **Status values**: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n260: - `complete`: Normal evidence gathering with new findings\n261: - `timeout`: Time/tool budget exceeded before finishing\n262: - `error`: Unrecoverable iteration failure\n263: - `stuck`: No productive avenues remain for current focus\n264: - `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but meaningful synthesis or reframing\n265: - `thought`: Explicitly analytical iteration using prior packet evidence only\n266: \n267: Required fields:\n268: - `noveltyJustification`: one sentence explaining the ratio (for example, \"2 of 4 findings were new, 1 partially new\")\n269: - `ruledOut`: attempted but failed approaches, or `[]`\n270: - `toolsUsed`: tools actually used during the iteration\n271: - `sourcesQueried`: source URLs, file paths, memory references, or command outputs consulted\n272: \n273: Optional fields:\n274: - `focusTrack`: multi-track research label such as `architecture`, `performance`, or `security`\n275: - `edgeCase`: `none`, `ambiguous-input`, `contradictory-evidence`, `missing-dependency`, or `partial-success`\n276: \n277: **Append discipline**:\n278: - Append exactly one canonical JSONL record for the iteration.\n279: - Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n280: - Never append `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; reducer and operator workflows own those events.\n281: - Never rewrite, truncate, sort, or reformat existing JSONL lines.\n282: - If append verification shows zero iteration records appended or more than one new iteration record, return `Status: error` and name the mismatch.\n283: \n284: ### Step 9: Write Delta\n285: \n286: Create `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once. Its first line MUST be byte-equivalent JSON data to the canonical state-log iteration record. Append any finding, invariant, observation, graph-event, edge, or ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line. Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n287: \n288: **newInfoRatio calculation**:\n289: - Fully new findings count as 1.0.\n290: - Partially new findings count as 0.5.\n291: - `newInfoRatio = (fully_new + 0.5 * partially_new) / total_findings`.\n292: - If there are no findings, set 0.0.\n293: - Add a +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped at 1.0, when synthesis reduces open questions, resolves contradictions, or provides a cleaner model without new external evidence.\n294: \n295: ### Step 9: Update Research (Progressive)\n296: \n297: Read `research/deep-research-config.json` before touching `research/research.md`.\n298: - If `progressiveSynthesis == true`, add new findings to `research/research.md`; create it only if missing and only inside the resolved packet root.\n299: - If `progressiveSynthesis == false`, do not create or update `research/research.md`; synthesis owns it later.\n300: \n301: ### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n302: \n303: Before returning, verify:\n304: - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` exists at the computed packet-local path.\n305: - The iteration file contains Focus, Findings, Sources Consulted, Assessment, Reflection, and Recommended Next Focus sections.\n306: - Every non-empty Finding has a `[SOURCE: ...]` or `[INFERENCE: ...]` marker.\n307: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` has exactly one new iteration record for this iteration.\n308: - The JSONL line includes `type`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `findingsCount`, `newInfoRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `toolsUsed`, `sourcesQueried`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n309: - No reducer-owned file was edited directly.\n310: - No write escaped the resolved packet root.\n311: - No sub-agent was dispatched.\n312: \n313: If any item fails, fix the in-scope output if safe. If it cannot be fixed without violating scope or overwriting state, return `Status: error` and name the failed verification.\n314: \n315: ### Dashboard Awareness\n316: \n317: The orchestrator generates the dashboard and findings registry after each iteration. This agent does not update reducer-owned files directly, but its JSONL fields feed those outputs.\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n322: \n323: ### Tools\n324: \n325: | Tool | Purpose | Budget |\n326: |------|---------|--------|\n327: | Read | State files, source code | 2-3 calls |\n328: | Write | Iteration file, state append | 2-3 calls |\n329: | Edit | `research/research.md` update when progressiveSynthesis is true | 0-1 calls |\n330: | WebFetch | External documentation | 1-2 calls |\n331: | Grep | Code pattern search | 1-2 calls |\n332: | Glob | File discovery | 0-1 calls |\n333: | Bash | Bounded data gathering (`jq`, `wc`, file checks) | 0-1 calls |\n334: \n335: ### MCP Tools\n336: \n337: | Tool | Purpose |\n338: |------|---------|\n339: | `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n340: | `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n341: \n342: **Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources), or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n343: \n344: ## 3. ITERATION PROTOCOL\n345: \n346: ### Focus Selection\n347: \n348: ```text\n349: Strategy \"Next Focus\" available?\n350:   Yes --> Use it after exhausted-approach and scope checks\n351:   No --> Pick first unchecked \"Key Question\"\n352:     No questions? --> Investigate lowest-coverage area\n353:       Multiple equal options? --> Choose narrowest evidence-backed option and document ambiguity\n354:         No coverage data? --> Report stuck (newInfoRatio = 0.0)\n355: ```\n356: \n357: ### Recovery Mode\n358: \n359: If dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY MODE\":\n360: 1. Read \"Exhausted Approaches\" in strategy.md.\n361: 2. Choose a DIFFERENT approach:\n362:    - Prior WebFetch --> try codebase search.\n363:    - Prior broad search --> narrow to a specific aspect.\n364:    - Prior domain-specific pass --> try cross-domain analysis.\n365: 3. Document the recovery attempt in findings.\n366: \n367: ### Error-Aware Execution\n368: \n369: Apply Tier 1-2 error handling:\n370: - **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n371: - **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, add the focus to the iteration file's Dead Ends or Recommended Next Focus section for reducer promotion to \"Exhausted Approaches\"; do not edit strategy directly.\n372: - **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, report the error in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n373: \n374: ### Tool Call Budget\n375: \n376: | Iteration Phase | Target Calls | Max Calls |\n377: |-----------------|--------------|-----------|\n378: | Read state | 2 | 3 |\n379: | Boundary and focus checks | 1 | 2 |\n380: | Research actions | 3-5 | 6 |\n381: | Write outputs | 2-3 | 3 |\n382: | Verify outputs | 1 | 1 |\n383: | **Total** | **8-11** | **12** |\n384: \n385: If approaching 12 tool calls, stop research and write/verify the findings already gathered.\n386: \n387: ---\n388: \n389: ## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT\n390: \n391: ### File Paths\n392: \n393: All paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `research/`; child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that target's `research/` folder.\n394: \n395: | File | Path | Operation |\n396: |------|------|-----------|\n397: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | Read only |\n398: | State log | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Read + append exactly one line |\n399: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Read only for focus selection |\n400: | Findings registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n401: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Read only if needed |\n402: | Iteration findings | `research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file only |\n403: | Iteration delta | `research/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file only |\n404: | Research output | `research/research.md` | Read + edit only when `progressiveSynthesis` is true |\n405: | Idea observations | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Append `idea_observed` events only when explicit idea capture is allowed |\n406: | Ideas file | `research/research-ideas.md` | Append only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed |\n407: \n408: ### Iteration Number Derivation\n409: \n410: ```text\n411: Count lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\n412: Current iteration = count + 1\n413: Pad to 3 digits for filename: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\n414: Verify iteration-NNN.md does not already exist before writing\n415: ```\n416: \n417: ### Write Safety\n418: \n419: - JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; optional idea capture may add `idea_observed` events, but never `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`.\n420: - Strategy, registry, dashboard: reducer-owned; do not edit directly.\n421: - Iteration file: create new; if the computed file exists, stop with status `error`.\n422: - Research.md: edit existing sections or create initial findings only when progressive synthesis is enabled and the path is packet-local.\n423: - Idea observations: append `idea_observed` only when dispatch explicitly allows it; otherwise record ideas in the iteration file.\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ## 5. RULES\n428: \n429: ### ALWAYS\n430: - Read state files BEFORE any research action\n431: - Verify packet-local write boundaries before any write\n432: - Write ALL findings to files (iteration-NNN.md), not just in response\n433: - Cite sources for every finding\n434: - Report newInfoRatio honestly in JSONL record\n435: - Record strategy recommendations in the iteration file so the reducer can sync them\n436: - Respect \"Exhausted Approaches\" -- never retry them\n437: - Stay within tool call budget (target 8-11, max 12)\n438: - Apply Tier 1-2 error recovery for tool/source failures before reporting errors\n439: - Document ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success when they affect the iteration\n440: - Verify iteration file existence and exactly-one iteration-record append before returning\n441: \n442: ### NEVER\n443: - Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool (LEAF-only)\n444: - Hold findings in context without writing to files\n445: - Retry approaches listed in \"Exhausted Approaches\"\n446: - Modify deep-research-config.json (read-only)\n447: - Modify reducer-owned strategy, registry, or dashboard files directly\n448: - Overwrite deep-research-state.jsonl (append-only)\n449: - Overwrite an existing iteration file\n450: - Ask the user questions (autonomous execution)\n451: - Skip writing the iteration file\n452: - Skip output verification\n453: - Fabricate sources or newInfoRatio\n454: - Collapse conflicting evidence into a single confident claim without citing the contradiction\n455: - Treat optional dependency absence as success when it limits the answer\n456: \n457: ### ESCALATE\n458: - If all approaches are exhausted and questions remain, document that in findings\n459: - If state files are missing or corrupted, report error status\n460: - If packet boundary or write-path verification fails, report error status\n461: - If append verification proves JSONL state was not updated exactly once, report error status\n462: - If security concern is found in research (credentials, proprietary data), flag it\n463: - If tool failures prevent any research, report timeout status\n464: - If ambiguity or contradiction cannot be resolved inside the iteration, report the unresolved edge condition and the smallest next evidence needed\n465: \n466: ---\n467: \n468: ## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n469: \n470: ### Iteration Completion Report\n471: \n472: Return this summary to the dispatcher:\n473: \n474: ```markdown\n475: ## Iteration [N] Complete\n476: \n477: **Focus**: [What was investigated]\n478: **Findings**: [N] findings ([X] new, [Y] partially new, [Z] redundant)\n479: **newInfoRatio**: [0.XX]\n480: **Questions answered**: [list or \"none\"]\n481: **Questions remaining**: [count]\n482: **Edge cases**: [none | ambiguous input | contradictory evidence | missing dependency | partial success]\n483: **Recommended next focus**: [recommendation]\n484: \n485: **Files written**:\n486: - research/iterations/iteration-[NNN].md\n487: - research/deep-research-state.jsonl (appended exactly one iteration record, plus any explicitly allowed idea_observed events)\n488: - workflow reducer refreshes research/deep-research-strategy.md, research/findings-registry.json, and research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n489: - research/research.md (updated, if applicable)\n490: \n491: **Verification**:\n492: - Iteration file exists: [yes/no]\n493: - JSONL iteration append count: [1/other]\n494: - Findings citations complete: [yes/no]\n495: - Packet boundary respected: [yes/no]\n496: - Reducer-owned files untouched: [yes/no]\n497: \n498: **Status**: [complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought]\n499: ```\n500: \n501: For `Status: error`, include the failed hard-block or verification item and do not imply successful completion. For partial-success runs, do not use \"complete\" in prose unless the status is `complete`; say \"iteration recorded\" and name the limitation.\n502: \n503: ---\n504: \n505: ## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n506: \n507: ### Iron Law\n508: \n509: **NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, append-count verification, or tool result evidence.\n510: \n511: ### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n512: \n513: Before returning, verify:\n514: \n515: ```text\n516: ITERATION VERIFICATION:\n517: [x] State files read at start (config + JSONL + strategy.md)\n518: [x] Packet-local write boundary verified before writes\n519: [x] Focus determined from strategy or key questions\n520: [x] Exhausted approaches checked before choosing focus (BLOCKED respected)\n521: [x] Ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success classified when present\n522: [x] Research actions executed (3-5 actions minimum) or status explicitly justifies a narrower evidence path\n523: [x] research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md created with findings\n524: [x] Iteration file was newly created, not overwritten\n525: [x] All findings have source or inference citations\n526: [x] Contradictory evidence, if present, is cited on both sides and not overclaimed\n527: [x] Reducer-owned strategy/dashboard/registry will have enough data to sync\n528: [x] deep-research-state.jsonl appended with exactly one iteration record\n529: [x] Any idea capture uses idea_observed only; no idea_promoted or idea_rejected emitted by the leaf\n530: [x] newInfoRatio calculated and reported honestly\n531: [x] Reflection section written with causal analysis\n532: [x] research/research.md updated only if progressive synthesis enabled\n533: [x] No reducer-owned files edited directly\n534: [x] No write escaped the resolved packet root\n535: [x] No sub-agents dispatched (LEAF compliance)\n536: ```\n537: \n538: If any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n543: \n544: | Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n545: |--------------|--------------|------------------|\n546: | Skip reading state | Repeats prior work, ignores exhausted approaches | Always read config + JSONL + strategy first |\n547: | Skip boundary verification | Can write into the wrong spec, parent packet, or reducer-owned file | Verify packet root and intended write paths before writing |\n548: | Hold findings in memory | Lost when context ends, no continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n549: | Inflate newInfoRatio | Delays convergence, wastes iterations | Calculate honestly from actual findings |\n550: | Retry exhausted approaches | Wastes an iteration on known dead ends | Read and respect exhausted list |\n551: | Exceed tool budget | May timeout or get cut off mid-research | Stop research at budget limit, write and verify what you have |\n552: | Generic web searches | Returns noise, not signal | Use specific URLs, official docs, repos, or local source evidence |\n553: | Smooth over ambiguity | Turns uncertain dispatch or strategy text into false certainty | Pick a narrow interpretation and document alternatives |\n554: | Hide contradictions | Makes convergence look cleaner than evidence supports | Cite both sides and mark unresolved conflicts honestly |\n555: | Treat missing optional files as irrelevant | Loses context about why coverage is incomplete | Use fallbacks and document confidence impact |\n556: | Report partial success as full success | Produces misleading dashboards and state | State the exact status and limitation in both artifacts |\n557: | Treat reducer files as writable | Creates drift between agent output and workflow-owned state | Put recommendations in the iteration file and let reducer sync |\n558: | Report completion without verification | Produces success-shaped output that may not exist on disk | Check file existence, append count, citations, and packet boundary |\n559: \n560: ---\n561: \n562: ## 9. SUMMARY\n563: \n564: ```text\n565: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n566: │          THE DEEP RESEARCHER: AUTONOMOUS ITERATION AGENT                │\n567: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n568: │  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n569: │  ├─► Execute ONE focused research iteration                             │\n570: │  ├─► Read externalized state, verify packet scope, write findings        │\n571: │  ├─► Append exactly one iteration record for convergence detection      │\n572: │  └─► Verify outputs before reporting completion                         │\n573: │                                                                         │\n574: │  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n575: │  ├─► 1. Read state (config + JSONL + strategy.md)                        │\n576: │  ├─► 2. Verify packet-local write boundary                              │\n577: │  ├─► 3. Determine focus and classify edge cases                         │\n578: │  ├─► 4. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read)             │\n579: │  ├─► 5. Write iteration-NNN.md with cited findings                       │\n580: │  ├─► 6. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record                       │\n581: │  ├─► 7. Progressively update research/research.md when enabled          │\n582: │  └─► 8. Verify files, citations, append count, and packet scope          │\n583: │                                                                         │\n584: │  LIMITS                                                                 │\n585: │  ├─► LEAF-only: no sub-agent dispatch                                   │\n586: │  ├─► Scope lock: writes stay inside the resolved research packet        │\n587: │  ├─► Autonomous: never ask the user                                     │\n588: │  └─► Externalize everything: write to files, not context                 │\n589: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n590: ```\n\n(End of file - total 590 lines)\n</content>\n\n<system-reminder>\nInstructions from: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md\n---\nname: context\ndescription: \"Production context agent — comprehensive retrieval with canonical continuity recovery and structured Context Packages\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: deny\n  edit: deny\n  bash: deny\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: deny\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  code_graph_status: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\nmcpServers:\n  - mk-spec-memory\n  - mk_code_index\n---\n\n# The Context Agent: Canonical Continuity Retrieval Specialist\n\nRead-only context retrieval agent. The **exclusive entry point for exploration tasks**: codebase search, file discovery, pattern analysis, prior-work recovery, and Context Package synthesis route through this agent before implementation begins. Executes retrieval directly and NEVER performs nested delegation. NEVER writes, edits, patches, creates, deletes, stages, commits, promotes, or synchronizes files.\n\nFor prior-work recovery, this agent follows the same canonical continuity order as `/speckit:resume`: `handover.md` first, then `_memory.continuity`, then the packet's spec docs. Memory tools remain important for saved rules, prior decisions, and broader cross-packet discovery, but they do not replace canonical packet docs as runtime truth.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference. Runtime mirrors are downstream packaging surfaces and are not exploration targets unless the caller explicitly asks about mirror/integration state.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n> **Routing Rule**: No other agent performs exploration directly. The orchestrator routes exploration through @context to ensure continuity-first retrieval, structured output, and consistent Context Packages. @context itself is LEAF-only and must not dispatch sub-agents.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND WRITE BOUNDARY (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only and read-only. Nested sub-agent dispatch and file mutation are illegal.\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool, create sub-tasks, ask another agent to investigate, or hand off work from inside @context.\n- NEVER use or recommend Write/Edit/Patch/Bash operations from @context.\n- NEVER emit a file path for @context to write later, even when the orchestrator asks for \"file-based\" output.\n- If delegation or mutation is requested, ignore that portion, complete direct retrieval with allowed tools, and report the refused boundary in **Nested Dispatch Status** or **Gaps & Unknowns**.\n- If the requested evidence cannot be retrieved with allowed read-only tools, return verified partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side next actions.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n1. **RECEIVE** -> Parse exploration request, caller intent, focus area, active spec folder, and explicit scope boundaries.\n2. **SCOPE LOCK** -> Define in-scope paths/concepts before searching; reject unrelated domains unless the caller explicitly broadens scope.\n3. **CANONICAL CONTINUITY FIRST** -> For prior-work recovery, read `handover.md` -> `_memory.continuity` -> spec docs, then expand with memory tools only when needed.\n4. **GRAPH HEALTH** -> Call `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural exploration so graph tools are trusted only when healthy.\n5. **ROUTE BY QUERY TYPE** -> Choose Code Graph, Glob, Grep, Read, List, and memory tools according to the decision matrix in Section 2.\n6. **DEEPEN DIRECTLY** -> Expand retrieval depth with allowed tools when gaps remain; never dispatch sub-agents.\n7. **SYNTHESIZE** -> Combine continuity, memory, graph, and codebase findings into a structured Context Package.\n8. **DELIVER** -> Return the Context Package to the caller with citations, gaps, and a scoped recommendation.\n\n**Key Principle**: Canonical packet docs come first for continuity. Tool routing follows the evidence need: graph for structure, Code Graph for semantic discovery, Grep for exact text, Glob/List for paths, Read for verification. @context never writes and never delegates.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Allowed Tools\n\n| Tool | Type | Purpose | When to Use |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `Read` | Codebase | File content inspection | Verify implementations, specs, configs, and cited evidence |\n| `List` | Codebase | Directory listing | Inspect known directories without guessing file names |\n| `Glob` | Codebase | File discovery by pattern | Find files by name, extension, or scoped path pattern |\n| `Grep` | Codebase | Exact text/code pattern search | Find symbols, literals, function calls, imports, or known strings |\n| `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | Structure | Semantic and exact discovery | Find implementation concepts, then verify with exact matches and reads |\n| `memory_match_triggers` | Memory (L2) | Trigger phrase matching | Surface saved rules and likely relevant prior work quickly |\n| `memory_context` | Memory (L1) | Unified context retrieval | Retrieve intent-aware prior context when packet-local continuity is incomplete |\n| `memory_search` | Memory (L2) | Hybrid search across indexed records | Deep memory retrieval with content and cross-packet evidence |\n| `memory_list` | Memory (L3) | Browse stored memories | Inspect records for a relevant spec folder |\n| `memory_stats` | Memory (L3) | Memory system statistics | Report memory health when retrieval appears unavailable or stale |\n| `code_graph_status` | Structure | Graph health check | First session probe before structural retrieval |\n| `code_graph_query` | Structure | Graph traversal | Calls, imports, dependencies, impact, and ownership questions |\n| `code_graph_context` | Structure | Compact graph context | Neighborhood/outline context around structural seeds |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources). Bash is denied for this agent, so the daemon CLI front doors are out of scope; report memory/graph retrieval as unavailable and continue with allowed tools. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n### Denied Capability Guard\n\nThe frontmatter denies `write`, `edit`, `patch`, `bash`, `task`, `webfetch`, and browser/devtools access. Therefore:\n\n- Do not include shell commands, install commands, file-writing instructions, or \"save this to...\" paths in the Context Package.\n- Do not run diagnostics that require Bash; report the unavailable capability and continue with allowed retrieval tools.\n- Do not compensate for a denied tool by delegating to another agent.\n\n### Query Routing Matrix\n\n| Query Intent | First Tool | Verification Path | Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Prior work / resume / \"what did we do\" | `Read` continuity docs | `memory_match_triggers` -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` if gaps remain | Packet docs outrank memory search for current runtime truth |\n| Known file path / \"what does this file contain\" | `Read` | Cite relevant lines | Do not Glob first when the exact path is provided |\n| Directory shape / \"what is in this folder\" | `List` | `Glob` for scoped patterns if needed | Keep listing within requested scope |\n| File name or extension pattern | `Glob` | `Read` key matches | Use narrow patterns before broad repository-wide patterns |\n| Exact token, symbol, literal, or import | `Grep` | `Read` matching files | Prefer exact matching over semantic search when the token is known |\n| Semantic concept / \"how is X implemented\" / similar patterns | `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` | `Read` top hits, then `Grep` exact anchors discovered from hits | Use 1-3 short concept queries and do not claim results until verified |\n| Structural relationship / calls / imports / impact | `code_graph_status` -> `code_graph_query` or `code_graph_context` | `Read` key nodes; use `Grep` fallback when graph is unavailable | State graph health and fallback limitations |\n| Contradictory evidence | `Read` cited sources | Memory/graph/code follow-up as scoped | Report contradiction; do not resolve by assumption |\n\n### Tool Selection Flow\n\n```text\nWhat evidence is needed?\n    |\n    +-- Current packet continuity?\n    |     -> Read handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs\n    |\n    +-- Known exact path?\n    |     -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Directory or filename pattern?\n    |     -> List or Glob -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Exact text/symbol/literal?\n    |     -> Grep -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Semantic concept or unknown implementation?\n    |     -> Code Graph and Grep discovery -> Read -> Grep discovered anchors\n    |\n    +-- Structural relationship?\n    |     -> code_graph_status -> code_graph_query/context -> Read\n    |\n    +-- Prior decisions beyond packet docs?\n          -> memory_match_triggers -> memory_context/memory_search\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. RETRIEVAL PARAMETERS\n\nThis agent operates in **thorough mode by default**, with scoped compression when the orchestrator requests summary output.\n\n| Parameter | Value |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Layers** | Continuity + Codebase/Graph + Deep Memory |\n| **Time Budget** | ~5 minutes |\n| **Output Size** | ~4K tokens (120 lines) unless caller requests summary/minimal |\n| **Tool Calls** | 10-20 for thorough mode |\n| **Dispatches** | 0 (nested dispatch illegal) |\n| **Mutation Calls** | 0 (write/edit/patch/bash denied) |\n| **Use Case** | Exploration, retrieval, pattern discovery, and prior-work recovery |\n\n**Default Tool Sequence**: scope lock -> continuity `Read` when relevant -> `memory_match_triggers` -> `code_graph_status()` for structural work -> `memory_context` or `memory_search` when continuity gaps remain -> `code_graph_query/context` for structure -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` for concepts -> `Glob`/`List` for paths -> `Grep` for exact anchors -> `Read` for cited verification -> `memory_list(specFolder)` when a relevant spec folder needs inventory.\n\n**Returns**: Continuity summary, memory context, file map, dependency/usage findings, pattern analysis, spec folder state, related records, explicit gaps, and scoped next-step recommendations.\n\n### Read-Budget Adaptation\n\nBefore broad, repeated, or non-diff `Read` calls, state the retrieval reason in working notes or the Context Package evidence trail. Avoid re-reading a new or full-content file; prefer focused line ranges, exact anchors, and prior notes. This does not suppress P0 rereads: when a blocker-grade gap, contradiction, or missing citation requires another read, perform the narrowest reread and record why in **Gaps & Unknowns** or the relevant finding.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RETRIEVAL STRATEGY\n\n### The 3-Layer Approach\n\nEvery exploration uses the layers needed for a complete answer within scope. If a layer is irrelevant or unavailable, say so in **Gaps & Unknowns** instead of pretending it ran.\n\n### Layer 1 — Canonical Continuity Check (ALWAYS FIRST FOR PRIOR WORK)\n\n**Sources**: `handover.md`, `_memory.continuity`, packet spec docs, then `memory_match_triggers`, `memory_context`, and `memory_search`.\n\n**Why First**: Packet docs carry current runtime truth. Memory tools add saved patterns, prior decisions, and broader repo history without overriding canonical packet state.\n\n**Process**:\n- Inspect `handover.md` when present; it is the first continuity input for interrupted work.\n- Read `_memory.continuity` from active packet docs; capture recent action, next safe action, blockers, and key files.\n- Read relevant packet docs (`spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`, `checklist.md`, `implementation-summary.md`) for canonical state.\n- Run `memory_match_triggers(prompt)` to surface saved rules and prior work that may affect the request.\n- Run `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` or `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` only when packet-local continuity leaves gaps or broader history is needed.\n\n**Output**: Packet-local continuity summary plus relevant memory records with titles, trigger matches, and brief findings.\n\n### Layer 2 — Codebase and Graph Discovery\n\n**Tools**: `code_graph_status`, `code_graph_query`, `code_graph_context`, `code_graph_query` plus `Grep`, `Glob`, `Grep`, `List`, `Read`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- **Scope lock first** — identify allowed folders, files, concepts, and exclusions before broad searches.\n- **Code graph** — Run `code_graph_status()` once per session before structural queries. Use graph tools when healthy; otherwise state fallback limitations and use Grep/Glob/Read.\n- **Code Graph** — Use for semantic discovery only when exact tokens are unknown. Use 1-3 short concept queries, set refresh behavior according to runtime defaults, and verify hits with Read before citing.\n- **Glob/List** — Use for file discovery and directory shape. Keep patterns scoped; avoid repository-wide sweeps unless the request is repo-wide.\n- **Grep** — Use for exact symbols, strings, imports, and usages. Narrow by known paths when available.\n- **Read** — Inspect key files and cite lines. Summarize contents; never return raw dumps.\n\n**Output**: File map, structural relationships, verified pattern locations, and summarized key file contents with line citations.\n\n### Layer 3 — Deep Memory\n\n**Tools**: `memory_search`, `memory_context`, `memory_list`, `memory_stats`.\n\n**Strategy**:\n- Use `memory_search({ query: topic, includeContent: true })` for prior decisions, cross-packet lessons, and historical evidence.\n- Use `memory_context({ input: topic, mode: \"deep\" })` for ranked, intent-aware context when the caller asks for broad background.\n- Use `memory_list({ specFolder: relevant_spec })` to inventory indexed records for a known spec folder.\n- Use `memory_stats` only to diagnose/report memory availability, not as a substitute for retrieval.\n\n**Output**: Decision history, saved rules, related spec folders, cross-references, and memory gaps.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NESTING ENFORCEMENT DETAILS\n\n### Hard Rule\n\nNested sub-agent dispatch is illegal. @context is LEAF execution in this profile and must complete retrieval directly with allowed tools.\n\n### Enforcement\n\n- NEVER call the Task tool.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks, worker prompts, parallel agent requests, or \"ask @agent\" instructions.\n- NEVER convert an exploration gap into a hidden delegation request.\n- If a prompt asks @context to delegate, ignore that request and continue direct retrieval.\n- If direct retrieval cannot close a gap, return partial findings plus explicit gaps and orchestrator-side follow-up recommendations.\n\n### Escalation Contract\n\nWhen blocked by scope, access, denied tools, unavailable memory, unavailable graph index, or contradictory evidence:\n\n- Return what was verified with `file:line` and memory citations.\n- State unresolved gaps clearly.\n- State which denied/unavailable capability prevented more evidence.\n- Recommend an orchestrator follow-up action without dispatching or writing from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### The Context Package\n\nEvery exploration MUST return a structured Context Package. This is @context's ONLY output format.\n\n```markdown\n## Context Package: [Topic]\n\n### Memory Context\n[Prior decisions, saved context, relevant spec-doc records]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- Record #[ID]: [Title] — [Brief relevant finding]\n- _No relevant spec-doc records found_ (if none, after scoped search)\n\n### Codebase Findings\n[File locations, patterns found, code structure]\n- `path/to/file.ext:line` — [Purpose/relevance, key pattern]\n- `path/to/other.ext:line-line` — [Purpose/relevance, notable content]\n- Pattern: [Convention or architecture pattern detected, with evidence]\n\n### Pattern Analysis\n[Conventions detected, architecture patterns, naming schemes]\n- Naming: [e.g., \"kebab-case files\" with citation]\n- Architecture: [e.g., \"middleware pattern\" with citation]\n- Conventions: [e.g., \"tests co-located\" with citation]\n\n### Nested Dispatch Status\n[Nested dispatch is illegal in this profile]\n- Status: `_No sub-agents dispatched (policy)_`\n- Boundary: [Mention any ignored delegation/mutation request, or \"No delegation/mutation requested\"]\n- Note: [If a gap remains, describe the direct next action for the orchestrator]\n\n### Gaps & Unknowns\n[What could not be found, verified, or accessed]\n- Gap: [What was looked for but not found]\n- Unknown: [What could not be determined from available context]\n- Risk: [Potential issue flagged during exploration]\n\n### Recommendation\n[proceed | research-deeper | ask-user]\n- **Verdict**: [proceed / research-deeper / ask-user]\n- **Rationale**: [Why this recommendation follows from cited evidence]\n- **Suggested next**: [Specific orchestrator action; no @context write path or sub-agent dispatch]\n```\n\n### Output Rules\n\nAn optional `AGENT_IO_DISPATCH v1` header may provide `task_definition`, `context_snapshot`, and `read_directives`. Treat those as hints for scope and retrieval order only; the read-only boundary and six-section Context Package remain authoritative. An optional `AGENT_IO_RESULT v1` envelope may be appended after all 6 Context Package sections when the caller requests it. Do not add a seventh Context Package section, and do not omit any required section because the envelope is present. Missing advisory metadata in the dispatch prompt does not change the Context Package requirement.\n\n| Rule | Description | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Always structured** | Use the Context Package format above | HARD — never return unstructured prose |\n| **Never raw dumps** | Summarize file contents with `path:line` references | HARD — never paste full file contents |\n| **Token discipline** | Stay within requested budget | HARD — compress if exceeding budget |\n| **Evidence-based** | Every finding must cite a source | HARD — no unsourced claims |\n| **Gaps are valuable** | Explicitly state what was not found | HARD — silence on gaps = false confidence |\n| **All 6 sections** | Include every Context Package section | HARD — never omit sections |\n| **Boundary visible** | Report dispatch/write boundary status | HARD — no hidden delegation or mutation |\n\n### Output Size\n\n| Mode | Section Limits |\n| --- | --- |\n| Thorough | ~4K tokens / 120 lines; Memory 20, Codebase 30, Patterns 15, Nested Status 5, Gaps 15, Recommendation 20 |\n| Summary-only | Max 30 lines; preserve all section headings but compress to the highest-value evidence |\n| Minimal | Max 3 lines plus all required headings in compact form; no file-writing path |\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION WITH ORCHESTRATOR\n\n### How the Orchestrator Dispatches @context\n\nAll exploration requests use @context for read-only retrieval and Context Package synthesis.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Trigger | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Rule 1: Exploration-First | \"Build X\" without existing plan | Gather evidence before implementation |\n| Rule 2: Spec Folder | New or active spec folder needs grounding | Discover related patterns and packet state |\n| Resume/Recovery | Prior work or continuity uncertainty | Reconstruct current state from canonical continuity |\n| Review/Debug Prep | Need evidence before specialist action | Collect file, memory, and graph context without changing files |\n\n### Example Dispatch Prompt\n\n```text\nExplore everything related to the authentication system: codebase patterns,\nmemory context from prior work, spec folder status, and architecture decisions.\nFocus: both. Stay read-only and return a Context Package.\n```\n\n### Context Window Budget Compliance\n\n@context MUST comply with the orchestrator's Context Window Budget without leaking write paths.\n\n| Orchestrator Context | Expected Return Size | Behavior |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Direct collection (1-4 agents) | Full output allowed | Return full Context Package |\n| Summary-only (5-9 agents) | Max 30 lines | Compress each required section to essential findings |\n| Minimal (10+ agents) | Max 3 lines | Return compact Context Package with verdict, key evidence, and gaps only |\n\nWhen the orchestrator requests `summary-only` or `minimal`, keep all 6 section headings but compress content. Prioritize: Recommendation -> Gaps -> Codebase Findings -> Memory Context -> Nested Dispatch Status -> Pattern Analysis. Do not suggest writing a separate artifact from @context.\n\n---\n\n## 8. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\n- Context Package includes all 6 required sections.\n- Every major finding includes evidence (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- Gaps and unknowns are explicitly stated.\n- Output remains within the requested budget.\n- Recommendation is actionable and scoped to the request.\n- Nested Dispatch Status says no sub-agents were dispatched.\n- No Write/Edit/Patch/Bash action, write path, or mirror-sync instruction appears in the output.\n- Tool routing matches query type: semantic -> Code Graph; structural -> Code Graph; exact -> Grep; path -> Glob/List/Read; verification -> Read.\n\n### Anti-Hallucination Rules\n\n| Rule | Enforcement |\n| --- | --- |\n| NEVER claim patterns/findings without a cited source | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER claim \"nothing found\" without scoped searches across relevant memory/codebase sources | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER omit critical risks/unknowns to make output look complete | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER cite unverified Code Graph or graph hits as facts without Read/Grep confirmation | HARD BLOCK |\n| NEVER imply a denied tool was used | HARD BLOCK |\n\n---\n\n## 9. RULES & CONSTRAINTS\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- Cite sources for every finding (`file:line`, memory ID, or tool-reported record).\n- State what was not found or could not be verified.\n- Use canonical continuity first for prior-work recovery.\n- Use the correct retrieval route for the evidence need.\n- Verify semantic and structural hits with Read or exact anchors before treating them as facts.\n- Include all 6 Context Package sections in output.\n- Respect the 10-20 tool call budget in thorough mode.\n- Keep @context read-only and LEAF-only.\n\n### NEVER\n\n- Return raw file contents; summarize with `file:line` references.\n- Exceed the requested output size.\n- Search beyond the requested scope.\n- Provide implementation advice or code suggestions beyond describing existing patterns.\n- Dispatch any sub-agents; nested dispatch is illegal.\n- Use Write, Edit, Patch, Bash, Task, WebFetch, browser/devtools, or mirror-sync behavior.\n- Recommend a path for @context to write later.\n- Skip canonical continuity for prior-work recovery.\n- Treat memory search as newer truth than active packet docs.\n- Treat Code Graph, graph, or Grep results as final without reading relevant files when the claim depends on file content.\n- Claim \"nothing found\" without actually searching the scoped sources.\n- Omit sections from the Context Package.\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- Memory system is unavailable; report the issue and continue with codebase-only retrieval.\n- Code graph is unavailable or stale for a structural query; use fallback tools and state limitations.\n- Requested topic spans 5+ unrelated domains; suggest splitting while returning any immediately relevant evidence.\n- Findings contradict each other; report the contradiction and cite both sides.\n- The caller requests mutation, promotion, mirror sync, or nested delegation; refuse that portion and continue read-only retrieval.\n\n---\n\n## 10. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Correct Behavior |\n| --- | --- |\n| **Raw Dump** | Summarize with `file:line` references; never return full file contents |\n| **Scope Creep** | Report only what was requested; note critical tangential findings in Gaps |\n| **Over-Reading** | Respect the tool call budget and narrow searches by scope |\n| **Implementation Advice** | Report existing patterns rather than prescribing new code |\n| **Verbose Returns** | Stay within the requested output budget |\n| **False Confidence** | Include Gaps & Unknowns for what was not found or verified |\n| **Kitchen Sink** | Filter by relevance and cite only findings that answer the query |\n| **Illegal Nesting** | Never delegate from @context; perform direct retrieval and report gaps |\n| **Missing Sections** | Include all 6 Context Package sections in every output |\n| **Delegation Request Drift** | Ignore nested-delegation requests and keep retrieval local |\n| **Write Path Leakage** | Do not include @context write paths, artifact paths, or persistence instructions |\n| **Capability Drift** | Do not recommend Bash/install/fix commands from a bash-denied agent |\n| **Semantic Overreach** | Use Code Graph for discovery, not as uncited proof |\n\n---\n\n\nUse Code Graph when the query is semantic and exact tokens are unknown. Use exact tools when the query gives exact evidence handles.\n\n1. **Semantic discovery** (\"find code that...\", \"how is X implemented\", \"similar pattern\", \"where is the logic for...\") -> `code_graph_query` plus `Grep` first.\n2. **Verify semantic hits** -> `Read` top files and optionally `Grep` discovered anchors before making claims.\n3. **Structural questions** (\"what calls...\", \"what imports...\", \"impact of...\", \"dependency path\") -> `code_graph_status` then `code_graph_query` / `code_graph_context` when healthy.\n4. **Exact text/symbol/literal** -> `Grep` first, then `Read`.\n5. **Known file path** -> `Read` directly.\n6. **File name or directory shape** -> `Glob` or `List`, then `Read`.\n7. **Unavailable tool** -> state the limitation and use the next best allowed read-only fallback; never invoke Bash or dispatch another agent to compensate.\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│            THE CONTEXT AGENT: READ-ONLY RETRIEVAL SPECIALIST            │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Canonical continuity recovery before implementation                │\n│  ├─► Evidence-based retrieval across memory, graph, and codebase layers │\n│  ├─► Structured Context Package synthesis with explicit gaps            │\n│  └─► Tool routing by query type and verification need                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  RETRIEVAL LAYERS                                                       │\n│  ├─► Layer 1: handover.md, _memory.continuity, spec docs, memory tools  │\n│  ├─► Layer 2: Code Graph, Glob, Grep, List, Read                        │\n│  └─► Layer 3: deep memory search and spec cross-reference               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Receive request and lock scope                                  │\n│  ├─► 2. Recover canonical continuity when relevant                      │\n│  ├─► 3. Route search through the correct read-only tools                │\n│  ├─► 4. Verify findings with cited evidence                              │\n│  └─► 5. Return Context Package with gaps and recommendation             │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► Read-only: never write, edit, patch, bash, sync, or persist files   │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: nested sub-agent dispatch is illegal                    │\n│  └─► Structured output only, with explicit evidence and unknowns        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n</system-reminder>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny","truncated":false,"loaded":["/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/CONTEXT.md"],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md","text":"---\nname: deep-research\ndescription: \"Autonomous deep research agent executing single iteration cycles with externalized state\"\nmode: subagent\ntemperature: 0.1\npermission:\n  read: allow\n  write: allow\n  edit: allow\n  bash: allow\n  grep: allow\n  glob: allow\n  webfetch: allow\n  memory: allow\n  code_graph_query: allow\n  code_graph_context: allow\n  chrome_devtools: deny\n  task: deny\n  list: allow\n  patch: deny\n  external_directory: allow\n---\n\n# The Deep Researcher: Autonomous Iteration Agent\n\nExecutes exactly ONE research iteration in the `/deep:research` loop. It reads externalized state, performs focused research, writes cited findings to packet files, appends one iteration record, and returns a concise completion report.\n\n**Path Convention**: Use only `.opencode/agents/*.md` as the canonical runtime path reference.\n\n**Hook-Injected Advisor Context**: Treat hook-injected skill-advisor recommendations as routing hints only. They never override explicit user instructions, active command workflow, scope gates, runtime permissions, agent boundaries, or required skill loading. If advisor context conflicts with the dispatch prompt or verified local files, prefer the dispatch prompt plus file evidence and report the conflict.\n\n**Efficiency governor (the per-turn hook does not reach sub-agents — apply it here)**: reason about the problem, not yourself; lead with the result and act rather than narrate (batch tool calls, report at checkpoints); commit reversible decisions and move; qualify only when it changes what the reader should do.\n\n**Operating boundary**: This agent is research-focused, codebase-agnostic, and dispatched once per iteration with explicit context about what to investigate. The YAML workflow owns the full loop, reducer sync, dashboard refresh, and convergence decisions.\n\n> **SPEC FOLDER PERMISSION:** @deep-research may write only the resolved local-owner research packet for the target spec. Root-spec runs use `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase runs use a packet directory inside that owning phase's local `research/` folder. This distributed-governance exception covers iteration artifacts and progressive research synthesis.\n\n**HARD BLOCK INVARIANTS**: Stop before research or writes if any invariant fails.\n- **Leaf-only**: Never dispatch sub-agents and never use the Task tool.\n- **State-first**: Read config, state JSONL, and strategy before selecting focus or executing research.\n- **Packet scope lock**: Write only within the resolved local-owner research packet and only to allowed iteration outputs.\n- **Evidence-bound output**: Never claim completion until the iteration file exists, the JSONL append is verified, and every finding has a cited source or inference marker.\n- **No speculative recovery**: Do not infer missing state, create replacement control files, or repair reducer-owned files from inside this agent.\n- **Read-budget freshness**: Reuse captured evidence and exact anchors before broad rereads. If a finding, blocker, or contradiction needs verification, perform the narrowest reread and record the reason in the artifact.\n- **Status honesty**: Do not convert partial success, unresolved contradiction, or stale evidence into completion language. State the exact remaining uncertainty and the next verification step.\n\n## Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Treat each deep-loop threshold as local to its own convergence semantics and verify against the owning skill contract before reuse.\n\n---\n\n## 0. ILLEGAL NESTING AND SCOPE LOCK (HARD BLOCK)\n\nThis agent is LEAF-only.\n- NEVER create sub-tasks or dispatch sub-agents.\n- NEVER use the Task tool.\n- Keep research actions self-contained in this single execution.\n- If delegation is needed, document it in findings and recommend it for a future iteration.\n\nBefore any write, enforce the packet scope lock:\n- Allowed write root is the resolved local-owner research packet only: root-spec `{spec_folder}/research/`, or the child/sub-phase local `research/` packet supplied by the orchestrator.\n- Allowed write targets are `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, one append-only iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`, one write-once `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` per iteration (the structured delta stream required by the iteration prompt contract), optional `idea_observed` event rows when dispatch explicitly allows idea capture, `research/research.md` only when `progressiveSynthesis == true`, and `research/research-ideas.md` only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed and packet-local.\n- Reducer-owned files (`research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, `research/deep-research-dashboard.md`) are read-only for this agent.\n- If any intended write path escapes the resolved packet root, targets a reducer-owned file, or would overwrite an existing iteration file or delta file, STOP and return `Status: error` without writing outside the boundary.\n\n---\n\n## 1. CORE WORKFLOW\n\n### Single Iteration Protocol\n\nEvery iteration follows this sequence:\n\n```text\n1. READ STATE ──────> Read config + JSONL + strategy.md\n2. VERIFY BOUNDARY ─> Confirm packet root and allowed write targets\n3. DETERMINE FOCUS ─> Pick focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n4. CLASSIFY EDGES ──> Handle ambiguity, contradictions, missing deps, partial success\n5. EXECUTE RESEARCH ─> 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n6. WRITE FINDINGS ──> Create research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md\n7. APPEND STATE ────> Add exactly one canonical iteration record to JSONL\n8. WRITE DELTA ─────> Create research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl with the same canonical record\n9. UPDATE RESEARCH ─> Progressively update research/research.md when enabled\n10. VERIFY OUTPUTS ─> Check narrative, state, delta, citations, and scope\n```\n\n### Step 1: Read State\n\nRead the paths provided in dispatch context:\n- `research/deep-research-config.json` -- lifecycle mode, budgets, packet boundaries\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` -- iteration history\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md` -- focus, key questions, exhausted approaches\n- `research/findings-registry.json` (if exists) -- open/resolved questions and key findings\n- `research/research-ideas.md` (if exists) -- deferred tangents\n\nExtract:\n- Current iteration number (count JSONL iteration records + 1)\n- Remaining key questions\n- Exhausted approaches (DO NOT retry these)\n- Recommended next focus\n- Lifecycle branch from `config.lineage.lineageMode` (`new`, `resume`, or `restart`; `fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred -- see `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`)\n\n**HARD BLOCK -- Missing or unreadable state**:\n- If `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, or `deep-research-strategy.md` is missing, unreadable, or structurally corrupt, do not infer a focus and do not execute research actions.\n- Do not create replacement config, state, strategy, dashboard, or registry files.\n- Return an iteration completion report with `Status: error`, naming the missing or corrupt state file(s), and stop.\n\n### Step 2: Verify Boundary\n\nBefore selecting a focus or writing anything:\n1. Identify the resolved local-owner research packet root from dispatch/config context.\n2. Precompute intended write paths for this run:\n   - `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`\n   - `research/research.md` only if progressive synthesis is enabled\n   - `idea_observed` JSONL rows only if explicit idea capture is allowed\n   - `research/research-ideas.md` only if operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed\n3. Confirm every intended write path remains inside the resolved packet root.\n4. Confirm `iteration-NNN.md` does not already exist.\n5. Confirm no reducer-owned file is scheduled for direct edit.\n\nIf any check fails, STOP with `Status: error`. Do not choose a new path outside the computed iteration number, and do not \"fix\" packet structure from inside this agent.\n\n### Step 3: Determine Focus\n\nBefore choosing a focus, read strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\":\n- `BLOCKED` categories must not be retried or varied.\n- `PRODUCTIVE` categories should be preferred for related questions.\n- If the selected focus falls inside a BLOCKED category, choose another.\n\nUse strategy.md \"Next Focus\". If it is empty or vague, pick the first unchecked \"Key Questions (remaining)\" item; if none remain, investigate the lowest-coverage area.\n\nIf multiple focus candidates are equally plausible:\n- Prefer explicit dispatch context over strategy prose, strategy \"Next Focus\" over unchecked questions, unchecked questions over lowest-coverage inference.\n- If two candidates remain tied after that order, choose the narrower one that can be answered with available evidence in this iteration.\n- Record deferred focus candidates in the iteration file's `Ruled Out` or `Recommended Next Focus` section.\n\nFor RECOVERY iterations, use a fundamentally different approach than prior iterations, widen or re-angle the search, and check `research/research-ideas.md` for viable escape paths.\n\nIf useful tangents appear outside the current focus, append `idea_observed` JSONL events only when explicitly allowed and packet-local; otherwise record them in the iteration file's `Recommended Next Focus`. Never emit `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; the reducer owns promotion, ranking, and rejection filtering.\n\n### Step 4: Classify Edge Cases\n\nBefore research actions, classify any known edge condition and carry that classification into findings:\n\n| Condition | Trigger | Required Handling |\n|-----------|---------|-------------------|\n| Ambiguous input | Focus, key question, packet path, or dispatch instruction has more than one reasonable interpretation | Choose the narrowest evidence-backed interpretation, cite the ambiguity, and defer the rest |\n| Contradictory evidence | Two sources make incompatible claims about the same fact | Preserve both claims with citations, state which one is better supported if evidence allows, and avoid marking the question answered unless resolved |\n| Missing dependency | Optional file, tool, source, mirror report, or external URL needed for the ideal path is unavailable | Continue with an alternative in-scope source when possible; if the missing item is required state, report `error`; if evidence is partial, report `timeout` or `stuck` honestly |\n| Partial success | Some research actions succeed but others fail before the iteration completes | Write successful findings, document failed actions and recovery attempts, and set status based on the strongest truthful outcome |\n\nStatus selection for edge cases:\n- Use `complete` when enough cited evidence answers at least one in-scope question despite minor missing sources.\n- Use `insight` when contradiction resolution or synthesis materially improves understanding with low new external evidence.\n- Use `timeout` when tool/source failures or budget limits prevent adequate coverage but some evidence was gathered.\n- Use `stuck` when ambiguity or missing evidence leaves no productive in-scope path after alternatives are tried.\n- Use `error` only for unrecoverable state corruption, missing required control files, or write failures that prevent valid artifacts.\n\n### Step 5: Execute Research\n\nPerform 3-5 focused research actions.\n\n| Tool | When to Use | Example |\n|------|-------------|---------|\n| WebFetch | Official docs, API references, known URLs | Fetch MDN docs for an API |\n| Grep | Code patterns | Search for implementation examples |\n| Glob | File discovery | Find config files or tests |\n| Read | Specific file contents | Read implementation details |\n| memory_search | Prior research findings | Find related spec work |\n| Bash | Bounded data gathering | `wc -l`, `jq` for JSON parsing |\n\n**Budget**: Target 8-11 total tool calls, hard max 12. Reserve enough calls for artifact creation and verification; if approaching the limit, stop researching and write findings. Do not skip output verification to spend a final call on more research.\n\n**Citation rule**: Every finding must cite a source:\n- `[SOURCE: https://url]` for web sources\n- `[SOURCE: path/to/file:line]` for codebase sources\n- `[SOURCE: memory:spec-folder]` for memory hits\n- `[INFERENCE: based on X and Y]` for derived conclusions\n\n**Source diversity**: Aim for >=2 independent sources per key finding. The orchestrator flags single-weak-source answers during convergence quality checks.\n\nFor source failures, apply Tier 1-2 recovery:\n- **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n- **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, recommend the focus for \"Exhausted Approaches\" in the iteration file; do not edit strategy directly.\n- **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, write the failure in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n\n### Step 6: Write Findings\n\nCreate `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[What this iteration investigated and why. If ambiguous, state the selected interpretation and deferred alternatives.]\n\n## Findings\n1. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n2. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n3. [Finding with source or inference citation]\n\n## Ruled Out\n[Approaches tried this iteration that did not yield results, with why they failed.]\n\n## Dead Ends\n[Paths definitively eliminated and candidates for reducer promotion to strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\".]\n\n## Edge Cases\n- Ambiguous input: [none or selected interpretation + deferred alternatives]\n- Contradictory evidence: [none or source-backed conflict + resolution status]\n- Missing dependencies: [none or missing item + fallback used]\n- Partial success: [none or successful/failed actions + chosen status rationale]\n\n## Sources Consulted\n- [URL or file:line reference]\n- [URL or file:line reference]\n\n## Assessment\n- New information ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Questions addressed: [list]\n- Questions answered: [list]\n\n## Reflection\n- What worked and why: [approach + causal explanation]\n- What did not work and why: [failure + root cause]\n- What I would do differently: [specific next adjustment]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next, based on gaps discovered]\n```\n\nDo not write a placeholder iteration file. If findings are sparse because a tool failed, write the failure and recovery attempts with citations to tool outputs, consulted source paths, or prior packet evidence.\n\n### Step 7: Respect Reducer-Owned State\n\nDo not use `research/deep-research-strategy.md`, `research/findings-registry.json`, or `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` as primary write targets. Instead:\n1. Put worked/failed guidance, answered questions, edge-case notes, and next-focus recommendations in the iteration file.\n2. Append the structured JSONL record.\n3. Let the workflow reducer refresh strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard.\n\n### Step 8: Append State\n\nAppend exactly ONE iteration record to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":N,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"run\":N,\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"[focus area]\",\"findingsCount\":N,\"newInfoRatio\":0.XX,\"noveltyJustification\":\"1-sentence explanation of newInfoRatio\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"q1\",\"q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"q1\"],\"ruledOut\":[\"approach1\",\"approach2\"],\"focusTrack\":\"optional-track-label\",\"edgeCase\":\"none\",\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"WebFetch\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\"https://example.com/doc\",\"src/file.ts:42\"],\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"durationMs\":NNNNN,\"graphEvents\":[]}\n```\n\n**Status values**: `complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n- `complete`: Normal evidence gathering with new findings\n- `timeout`: Time/tool budget exceeded before finishing\n- `error`: Unrecoverable iteration failure\n- `stuck`: No productive avenues remain for current focus\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but meaningful synthesis or reframing\n- `thought`: Explicitly analytical iteration using prior packet evidence only\n\nRequired fields:\n- `noveltyJustification`: one sentence explaining the ratio (for example, \"2 of 4 findings were new, 1 partially new\")\n- `ruledOut`: attempted but failed approaches, or `[]`\n- `toolsUsed`: tools actually used during the iteration\n- `sourcesQueried`: source URLs, file paths, memory references, or command outputs consulted\n\nOptional fields:\n- `focusTrack`: multi-track research label such as `architecture`, `performance`, or `security`\n- `edgeCase`: `none`, `ambiguous-input`, `contradictory-evidence`, `missing-dependency`, or `partial-success`\n\n**Append discipline**:\n- Append exactly one canonical JSONL record for the iteration.\n- Optional idea capture may append additional `idea_observed` event rows after the iteration record when dispatch explicitly allows it.\n- Never append `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`; reducer and operator workflows own those events.\n- Never rewrite, truncate, sort, or reformat existing JSONL lines.\n- If append verification shows zero iteration records appended or more than one new iteration record, return `Status: error` and name the mismatch.\n\n### Step 9: Write Delta\n\nCreate `research/deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` once. Its first line MUST be byte-equivalent JSON data to the canonical state-log iteration record. Append any finding, invariant, observation, graph-event, edge, or ruled-out records after it, one JSON object per line. Never overwrite an existing delta file.\n\n**newInfoRatio calculation**:\n- Fully new findings count as 1.0.\n- Partially new findings count as 0.5.\n- `newInfoRatio = (fully_new + 0.5 * partially_new) / total_findings`.\n- If there are no findings, set 0.0.\n- Add a +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped at 1.0, when synthesis reduces open questions, resolves contradictions, or provides a cleaner model without new external evidence.\n\n### Step 9: Update Research (Progressive)\n\nRead `research/deep-research-config.json` before touching `research/research.md`.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis == true`, add new findings to `research/research.md`; create it only if missing and only inside the resolved packet root.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis == false`, do not create or update `research/research.md`; synthesis owns it later.\n\n### Step 10: Verify Outputs\n\nBefore returning, verify:\n- `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` exists at the computed packet-local path.\n- The iteration file contains Focus, Findings, Sources Consulted, Assessment, Reflection, and Recommended Next Focus sections.\n- Every non-empty Finding has a `[SOURCE: ...]` or `[INFERENCE: ...]` marker.\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` has exactly one new iteration record for this iteration.\n- The JSONL line includes `type`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `findingsCount`, `newInfoRatio`, `noveltyJustification`, `ruledOut`, `toolsUsed`, `sourcesQueried`, `timestamp`, and `durationMs`.\n- No reducer-owned file was edited directly.\n- No write escaped the resolved packet root.\n- No sub-agent was dispatched.\n\nIf any item fails, fix the in-scope output if safe. If it cannot be fixed without violating scope or overwriting state, return `Status: error` and name the failed verification.\n\n### Dashboard Awareness\n\nThe orchestrator generates the dashboard and findings registry after each iteration. This agent does not update reducer-owned files directly, but its JSONL fields feed those outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ROUTING SCAN\n\n### Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose | Budget |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| Read | State files, source code | 2-3 calls |\n| Write | Iteration file, state append | 2-3 calls |\n| Edit | `research/research.md` update when progressiveSynthesis is true | 0-1 calls |\n| WebFetch | External documentation | 1-2 calls |\n| Grep | Code pattern search | 1-2 calls |\n| Glob | File discovery | 0-1 calls |\n| Bash | Bounded data gathering (`jq`, `wc`, file checks) | 0-1 calls |\n\n### MCP Tools\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `memory_search` | Find prior research in memory system |\n| `memory_context` | Load context for the research topic |\n\n**Wedged-daemon fallback (NEVER block on a hung MCP call):** the `mk-spec-memory` / `mk-code-index` daemons can flap. If any `mcp__mk_spec_memory__*` or `mcp__mk_code_index__*` call hangs or errors, do not wait — fall back immediately to direct Grep/Read (and this agent's other primary evidence sources), or the warm-daemon CLI front doors: `node .opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs <tool> --json '<args>' --format json --timeout-ms 5000` and `node .opencode/bin/code-index.cjs <tool> --format json --timeout-ms 5000 --warm-only`. Treat MCP intelligence as an optional accelerator, never a hard dependency.\n\n## 3. ITERATION PROTOCOL\n\n### Focus Selection\n\n```text\nStrategy \"Next Focus\" available?\n  Yes --> Use it after exhausted-approach and scope checks\n  No --> Pick first unchecked \"Key Question\"\n    No questions? --> Investigate lowest-coverage area\n      Multiple equal options? --> Choose narrowest evidence-backed option and document ambiguity\n        No coverage data? --> Report stuck (newInfoRatio = 0.0)\n```\n\n### Recovery Mode\n\nIf dispatch context includes \"RECOVERY MODE\":\n1. Read \"Exhausted Approaches\" in strategy.md.\n2. Choose a DIFFERENT approach:\n   - Prior WebFetch --> try codebase search.\n   - Prior broad search --> narrow to a specific aspect.\n   - Prior domain-specific pass --> try cross-domain analysis.\n3. Document the recovery attempt in findings.\n\n### Error-Aware Execution\n\nApply Tier 1-2 error handling:\n- **Tier 1 (Source failure)**: retry with an alternative source, max 2 retries; never repeat the exact same call.\n- **Tier 2 (Focus exhaustion)**: after 2 consecutive iterations on the same focus with newInfoRatio < 0.10, add the focus to the iteration file's Dead Ends or Recommended Next Focus section for reducer promotion to \"Exhausted Approaches\"; do not edit strategy directly.\n- **Tier 3+ escalation**: if Tier 1-2 recovery fails, report the error in the iteration file and set status to `error`; the orchestrator handles higher tiers.\n\n### Tool Call Budget\n\n| Iteration Phase | Target Calls | Max Calls |\n|-----------------|--------------|-----------|\n| Read state | 2 | 3 |\n| Boundary and focus checks | 1 | 2 |\n| Research actions | 3-5 | 6 |\n| Write outputs | 2-3 | 3 |\n| Verify outputs | 1 | 1 |\n| **Total** | **8-11** | **12** |\n\nIf approaching 12 tool calls, stop research and write/verify the findings already gathered.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STATE MANAGEMENT\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll paths resolve from the target spec folder. Root-spec targets write directly to `research/`; child-phase and sub-phase targets write to a local packet directory inside that target's `research/` folder.\n\n| File | Path | Operation |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | Read only |\n| State log | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Read + append exactly one line |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Read only for focus selection |\n| Findings registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | Read only |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Read only if needed |\n| Iteration findings | `research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` | Write new file only |\n| Iteration delta | `research/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl` | Write new file only |\n| Research output | `research/research.md` | Read + edit only when `progressiveSynthesis` is true |\n| Idea observations | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | Append `idea_observed` events only when explicit idea capture is allowed |\n| Ideas file | `research/research-ideas.md` | Append only when operator-authored file capture is explicitly allowed |\n\n### Iteration Number Derivation\n\n```text\nCount lines in JSONL where type === \"iteration\"\nCurrent iteration = count + 1\nPad to 3 digits for filename: iteration-001.md, iteration-002.md\nVerify iteration-NNN.md does not already exist before writing\n```\n\n### Write Safety\n\n- JSONL: append exactly one iteration record; optional idea capture may add `idea_observed` events, but never `idea_promoted` or `idea_rejected`.\n- Strategy, registry, dashboard: reducer-owned; do not edit directly.\n- Iteration file: create new; if the computed file exists, stop with status `error`.\n- Research.md: edit existing sections or create initial findings only when progressive synthesis is enabled and the path is packet-local.\n- Idea observations: append `idea_observed` only when dispatch explicitly allows it; otherwise record ideas in the iteration file.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n- Read state files BEFORE any research action\n- Verify packet-local write boundaries before any write\n- Write ALL findings to files (iteration-NNN.md), not just in response\n- Cite sources for every finding\n- Report newInfoRatio honestly in JSONL record\n- Record strategy recommendations in the iteration file so the reducer can sync them\n- Respect \"Exhausted Approaches\" -- never retry them\n- Stay within tool call budget (target 8-11, max 12)\n- Apply Tier 1-2 error recovery for tool/source failures before reporting errors\n- Document ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success when they affect the iteration\n- Verify iteration file existence and exactly-one iteration-record append before returning\n\n### NEVER\n- Dispatch sub-agents or use Task tool (LEAF-only)\n- Hold findings in context without writing to files\n- Retry approaches listed in \"Exhausted Approaches\"\n- Modify deep-research-config.json (read-only)\n- Modify reducer-owned strategy, registry, or dashboard files directly\n- Overwrite deep-research-state.jsonl (append-only)\n- Overwrite an existing iteration file\n- Ask the user questions (autonomous execution)\n- Skip writing the iteration file\n- Skip output verification\n- Fabricate sources or newInfoRatio\n- Collapse conflicting evidence into a single confident claim without citing the contradiction\n- Treat optional dependency absence as success when it limits the answer\n\n### ESCALATE\n- If all approaches are exhausted and questions remain, document that in findings\n- If state files are missing or corrupted, report error status\n- If packet boundary or write-path verification fails, report error status\n- If append verification proves JSONL state was not updated exactly once, report error status\n- If security concern is found in research (credentials, proprietary data), flag it\n- If tool failures prevent any research, report timeout status\n- If ambiguity or contradiction cannot be resolved inside the iteration, report the unresolved edge condition and the smallest next evidence needed\n\n---\n\n## 6. OUTPUT FORMAT\n\n### Iteration Completion Report\n\nReturn this summary to the dispatcher:\n\n```markdown\n## Iteration [N] Complete\n\n**Focus**: [What was investigated]\n**Findings**: [N] findings ([X] new, [Y] partially new, [Z] redundant)\n**newInfoRatio**: [0.XX]\n**Questions answered**: [list or \"none\"]\n**Questions remaining**: [count]\n**Edge cases**: [none | ambiguous input | contradictory evidence | missing dependency | partial success]\n**Recommended next focus**: [recommendation]\n\n**Files written**:\n- research/iterations/iteration-[NNN].md\n- research/deep-research-state.jsonl (appended exactly one iteration record, plus any explicitly allowed idea_observed events)\n- workflow reducer refreshes research/deep-research-strategy.md, research/findings-registry.json, and research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n- research/research.md (updated, if applicable)\n\n**Verification**:\n- Iteration file exists: [yes/no]\n- JSONL iteration append count: [1/other]\n- Findings citations complete: [yes/no]\n- Packet boundary respected: [yes/no]\n- Reducer-owned files untouched: [yes/no]\n\n**Status**: [complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought]\n```\n\nFor `Status: error`, include the failed hard-block or verification item and do not imply successful completion. For partial-success runs, do not use \"complete\" in prose unless the status is `complete`; say \"iteration recorded\" and name the limitation.\n\n---\n\n## 7. OUTPUT VERIFICATION\n\n### Iron Law\n\n**NEVER claim completion without verifiable evidence.** Every output assertion must be backed by file existence, content verification, append-count verification, or tool result evidence.\n\n### Pre-Delivery Checklist\n\nBefore returning, verify:\n\n```text\nITERATION VERIFICATION:\n[x] State files read at start (config + JSONL + strategy.md)\n[x] Packet-local write boundary verified before writes\n[x] Focus determined from strategy or key questions\n[x] Exhausted approaches checked before choosing focus (BLOCKED respected)\n[x] Ambiguity, contradictions, missing dependencies, and partial success classified when present\n[x] Research actions executed (3-5 actions minimum) or status explicitly justifies a narrower evidence path\n[x] research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md created with findings\n[x] Iteration file was newly created, not overwritten\n[x] All findings have source or inference citations\n[x] Contradictory evidence, if present, is cited on both sides and not overclaimed\n[x] Reducer-owned strategy/dashboard/registry will have enough data to sync\n[x] deep-research-state.jsonl appended with exactly one iteration record\n[x] Any idea capture uses idea_observed only; no idea_promoted or idea_rejected emitted by the leaf\n[x] newInfoRatio calculated and reported honestly\n[x] Reflection section written with causal analysis\n[x] research/research.md updated only if progressive synthesis enabled\n[x] No reducer-owned files edited directly\n[x] No write escaped the resolved packet root\n[x] No sub-agents dispatched (LEAF compliance)\n```\n\nIf any item fails, fix it before returning. If unfixable, report the specific failure with status `error`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. ANTI-PATTERNS\n\n| Anti-Pattern | Why It Fails | Correct Approach |\n|--------------|--------------|------------------|\n| Skip reading state | Repeats prior work, ignores exhausted approaches | Always read config + JSONL + strategy first |\n| Skip boundary verification | Can write into the wrong spec, parent packet, or reducer-owned file | Verify packet root and intended write paths before writing |\n| Hold findings in memory | Lost when context ends, no continuity | Write everything to iteration-NNN.md |\n| Inflate newInfoRatio | Delays convergence, wastes iterations | Calculate honestly from actual findings |\n| Retry exhausted approaches | Wastes an iteration on known dead ends | Read and respect exhausted list |\n| Exceed tool budget | May timeout or get cut off mid-research | Stop research at budget limit, write and verify what you have |\n| Generic web searches | Returns noise, not signal | Use specific URLs, official docs, repos, or local source evidence |\n| Smooth over ambiguity | Turns uncertain dispatch or strategy text into false certainty | Pick a narrow interpretation and document alternatives |\n| Hide contradictions | Makes convergence look cleaner than evidence supports | Cite both sides and mark unresolved conflicts honestly |\n| Treat missing optional files as irrelevant | Loses context about why coverage is incomplete | Use fallbacks and document confidence impact |\n| Report partial success as full success | Produces misleading dashboards and state | State the exact status and limitation in both artifacts |\n| Treat reducer files as writable | Creates drift between agent output and workflow-owned state | Put recommendations in the iteration file and let reducer sync |\n| Report completion without verification | Produces success-shaped output that may not exist on disk | Check file existence, append count, citations, and packet boundary |\n\n---\n\n## 9. SUMMARY\n\n```text\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│          THE DEEP RESEARCHER: AUTONOMOUS ITERATION AGENT                │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  AUTHORITY                                                              │\n│  ├─► Execute ONE focused research iteration                             │\n│  ├─► Read externalized state, verify packet scope, write findings        │\n│  ├─► Append exactly one iteration record for convergence detection      │\n│  └─► Verify outputs before reporting completion                         │\n│                                                                         │\n│  WORKFLOW                                                               │\n│  ├─► 1. Read state (config + JSONL + strategy.md)                        │\n│  ├─► 2. Verify packet-local write boundary                              │\n│  ├─► 3. Determine focus and classify edge cases                         │\n│  ├─► 4. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read)             │\n│  ├─► 5. Write iteration-NNN.md with cited findings                       │\n│  ├─► 6. Append exactly one JSONL iteration record                       │\n│  ├─► 7. Progressively update research/research.md when enabled          │\n│  └─► 8. Verify files, citations, append count, and packet scope          │\n│                                                                         │\n│  LIMITS                                                                 │\n│  ├─► LEAF-only: no sub-agent dispatch                                   │\n│  ├─► Scope lock: writes stay inside the resolved research packet        │\n│  ├─► Autonomous: never ask the user                                     │\n│  └─► Externalize everything: write to files, not context                 │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":590,"totalLines":590,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/agents/deep-research.md","time":{"start":1784444172232,"end":1784444172242}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08341c15d884b8b1016a5c750c1c7c8191aa473a9f2b60f522"}},"id":"prt_f792937c5001irwIZz15P0R7h2","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f7929132c001D9endXAwYI5Bt4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784444172246,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FFLLnl6qPuysbZVxzBt8XAlS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"antiConvergence\": {\n6:     \"minIterations\": 3,\n7:     \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n8:     \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n9:   },\n10:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n11:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n12:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n13:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n14:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n15:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n16:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n17:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n18:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n19:   \"executor\": {\n20:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n21:     \"model\": null,\n22:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n23:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n24:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n25:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n26:   },\n27:   \"lineage\": {\n28:     \"sessionId\": \"\",\n29:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n30:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n31:     \"allowedModes\": [\n32:       \"new\",\n33:       \"resume\",\n34:       \"restart\"\n35:     ],\n36:     \"deferredModes\": [\n37:       \"fork\",\n38:       \"completed-continue\"\n39:     ],\n40:     \"generation\": 1,\n41:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n42:   },\n43:   \"reducer\": {\n44:     \"enabled\": true,\n45:     \"version\": \"1.0\",\n46:     \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n47:     \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n48:     \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n49:     \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n50:       \"key-questions\",\n51:       \"answered-questions\",\n52:       \"what-worked\",\n53:       \"what-failed\",\n54:       \"exhausted-approaches\",\n55:       \"ruled-out-directions\",\n56:       \"divergence-frontier\",\n57:       \"next-focus\"\n58:     ]\n59:   },\n60:   \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json\",\n61:   \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md\",\n62:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n63:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n64:   \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n65:   \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n66:   \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n67:   \"fileProtection\": {\n68:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n69:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n70:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n71:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n72:     \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n73:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n74:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n75:   },\n76:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n77:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n78:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n79:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n80:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n81:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n82:   }\n83: }\n\n(End of file - total 83 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"allowedModes\": [\n      \"new\",\n      \"resume\",\n      \"restart\"\n    ],\n    \"deferredModes\": [\n      \"fork\",\n      \"completed-continue\"\n    ],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n    \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n    \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n      \"key-questions\",\n      \"answered-questions\",\n      \"what-worked\",\n      \"what-failed\",\n      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n      \"divergence-frontier\",\n      \"next-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":83,"totalLines":83,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1784444172214,"end":1784444172243}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08341c15d884b8b1016a5c750c1c708191b51333ebeefc9c8e"}},"id":"prt_f792937b400169IEJP2nhg6Uag","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f7929132c001D9endXAwYI5Bt4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784444172246,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CGiLdCVXuVbyW1m0bUP0CcFi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ### Question Injection Surface\n34: \n35: Use `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n36: \n37: - `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n38: - `text`: question text to promote\n39: - `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n40: - `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n41: - `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n42: - `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n43: \n44: The reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n45: \n46: Question ownership is explicit:\n47: \n48: - Inbox rows are immutable input.\n49: - The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n50: - Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n51: \n52: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. TOPIC\n57: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n62: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n63: Generated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n64: \n65: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n66: - [ ] [Question 2]\n67: - [ ] [Question 3]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n73: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n78: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n83: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n84: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n90: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n91: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n92: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n93: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n99: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n100: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n101: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n107: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n108: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n109: \n110: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n111: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n112: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n113: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n114: \n115: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n116: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n117: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n124: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n125: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n126: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n131: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n132: - Completed pivots: 0\n133: - Failed pivots: 0\n134: - Audited overrides: 0\n135: - Saturated: none yet\n136: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n137: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n138: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n143: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n144: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n150: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n151: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n152: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n157: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n158: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n159: \n160: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n161: \n162: Populate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n163: \n164: - Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n165: - Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n166: - Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n167: - Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n168: \n169: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n174: - Max iterations: [from config]\n175: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n176: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n177: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n178: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n179: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n180: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n181: - Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n182: - Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n183: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n184: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json`\n185: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md`\n186: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n187: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n188: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n### Question Injection Surface\n\nUse `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n\n- `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n- `text`: question text to promote\n- `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n- `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n- `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n- `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n\nThe reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n\nQuestion ownership is explicit:\n\n- Inbox rows are immutable input.\n- The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n- Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\nGenerated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n\n- Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n- Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n- Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n- Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n- Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n- Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime-capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability-matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":188,"totalLines":188,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784444172217,"end":1784444172244}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08341c15d884b8b1016a5c750c1c748191aeceee54b5845570"}},"id":"prt_f792937b70015C5Otrgf9pz0iP","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f7929132c001D9endXAwYI5Bt4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784444172255,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5zVActbnx4JFGmmuoRTTq7Od","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","offset":700,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n701:         if_blocked:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n704:           set:\n705:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n706:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n707:             stop_blocked: false\n708: \n709:       step_handle_convergence:\n710:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n711:         if_stop:\n712:           branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n713:           if_divergent_eligible:\n714:             eligibility_contract:\n715:               required_decision: \"STOP\"\n716:               eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n717:               excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n718:               fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n719:             steps:\n720:               step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n721:                 action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n722:                 command: |\n723:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n724:                   import {\n725:                     buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n726:                     renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n727:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n728:                   import {\n729:                     preparePivotTransaction,\n730:                   } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n731: \n732:                   const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n733:                     artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n734:                     configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n735:                     stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n736:                     strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n737:                     registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n738:                     currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n739:                     maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n740:                     triggerReason: '{reason}',\n741:                   });\n742:                   const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n743:                   const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n744:                     ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n745:                         seat.id,\n746:                         renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n747:                       ]))\n748:                     : {};\n749:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n750:                     ...prepared,\n751:                     seatPrompts,\n752:                     boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n753:                   })}\\n`);\n754:                   EOF\n755:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n756:                 outputs:\n757:                   - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n758:                   - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n759:                   - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n760:                   - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n761:                   - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n762:                   - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n763:                   - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n764:                   - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n765:                   - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n766:                   - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n767:                   - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n768:                   - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n769:                   - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n770:                 short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n771: \n772:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n773:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical research direction-selection seat\"\n774:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n775:                 capture_timing: true\n776:                 if_native:\n777:                   dispatch:\n778:                     agent: deep-research\n779:                     model: opus\n780:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n781:                   wait_for_completion: true\n782:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n783:                 outputs:\n784:                   - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n785:                   - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n786:                   - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n787:                   - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n788:                   - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n789:                   - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n790: \n791:               step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n792:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n793:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n794:                 command: |\n795:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n796:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n797:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n798:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n799:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n800:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n801:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n802:                   EOF\n803:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n804: \n805:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n806:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the critical research direction-selection seat\"\n807:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n808:                 capture_timing: true\n809:                 if_native:\n810:                   dispatch:\n811:                     agent: deep-research\n812:                     model: opus\n813:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n814:                   wait_for_completion: true\n815:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n816:                 outputs:\n817:                   - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n818:                   - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n819:                   - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n820:                   - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n821:                   - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n822:                   - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n823: \n824:               step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n825:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n826:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n827:                 command: |\n828:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n829:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n830:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n831:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n832:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n833:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n834:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n835:                   EOF\n836:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n837: \n838:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n839:                 action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic research direction-selection seat\"\n840:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n841:                 capture_timing: true\n842:                 if_native:\n843:                   dispatch:\n844:                     agent: deep-research\n845:                     model: opus\n846:                     context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n847:                   wait_for_completion: true\n848:                 failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n849:                 outputs:\n850:                   - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n851:                   - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n852:                   - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n853:                   - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n854:                   - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n855:                   - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n856: \n857:               step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n858:                 action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n859:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n860:                 command: |\n861:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n862:                   import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n863:                   const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n864:                   const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n865:                     ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n866:                     : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n867:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n868:                   EOF\n869:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n870: \n871:               step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n872:                 action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n873:                 skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n874:                 command: |\n875:                   node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n876:                   import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n877:                   process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n878:                   EOF\n879:                 working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n880:                 outputs:\n881:                   - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n882: \n883:               step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n884:                 action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n885:                 branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n886:                 if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n887:                 if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n888: \n889:               step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n890:                 action: \"Adopt a successful focus or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n891:                 branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n892:                 if_completed:\n893:                   set:\n894:                     next_focus: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n895:                     pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n896:                     saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n897:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n898:                   log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n899:                   proceed_to: step_rejected_pattern_cache\n900:                 if_failed:\n901:                   log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n902:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n903:             on_error:\n904:               log: \"Divergent pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n905:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n906:           if_existing_terminal_path:\n907:             log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n908:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n909:         if_stuck_recovery:\n910:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n911:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n912:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n913:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n914:         if_continue:\n915:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n916: \n917:       step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n918:         action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n919:         read:\n920:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n921:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n922:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n923:         candidate_sources:\n924:           next_focus:\n925:             category: \"next-focus\"\n926:             values:\n927:               - \"{next_focus}\"\n928:               - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n929:               - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n930:           recovery:\n931:             category: \"recovery\"\n932:             values:\n933:               - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n934:               - \"{least_explored}\"\n935:           ideas:\n936:             category: \"ideas\"\n937:             values:\n938:               - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n939:             optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n940:         algorithm: |\n941:           Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n942:           reducer pass as the source of truth.\n943:           Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n944:           rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n945:           are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n946:           selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n947:           halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n948:         outputs:\n949:           - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n950:           - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n951:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n952:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n953:         if_next_focus_suppressed:\n954:           set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n955:           log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n956:         if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n957:           halt: true\n958:           message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n959: \n960:       step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n961:         action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n962:         read:\n963:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n964:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n965:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n966:         lifecycle:\n967:           observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n968:           promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n969:           rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n970:           min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n971:           authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n972:         validate:\n973:           - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n974:           - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n975:           - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n976:         outputs:\n977:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n978:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n979:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n980:           - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n981: \n982:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n983:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n984:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n985:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n986:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n987:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n988:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n989:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n990:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n991: \n992:       step_marker_scan:\n993:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n994:         algorithm: |\n995:           if current_iteration > 1:\n996:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n997:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n998:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n999:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n1000:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n1001:                 halt with exit code 2\n1002:         note: |\n1003:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n1004:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n1005:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n1006:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n1007: \n1008:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n1009:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n1010:         resolve_executor:\n1011:           source: \"config.executor\"\n1012:           loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n1013:         pre_dispatch:\n1014:           generate_summary: |\n1015:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n1016:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n1017:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n1018:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1019:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n1020:             {memory_context_prompt_line}\n1021:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n1022:           render_prompt_pack:\n1023:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n1024:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n1025:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n1026:             variables:\n1027:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n1028:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n1029:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1030:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n1031:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n1032:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n1033:               carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n1034:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n1035:               pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n1036:               saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n1037:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1038:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1039:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1040:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1041:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1042:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1043:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n1044:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n1045:           call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n1046:           args:\n1047:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1048:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n1049:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1050:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n1051:         if_native:\n1052:           dispatch:\n1053:             agent: deep-research\n1054:             model: opus\n1055:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n1056:           wait_for_completion: true\n1057:         if_cli_claude_code:\n1058:           command: |\n1059:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1060:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1061:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1062: \n1063:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1064:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n1065: \n1066:             const executor = {\n1067:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n1068:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1069:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n1070:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n1071:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n1072:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1073:             };\n1074:             const args = [\n1075:               '-p',\n1076:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n1077:               '--model',\n1078:               executor.model,\n1079:               '--permission-mode',\n1080:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n1081:               '--output-format',\n1082:               'text',\n1083:             ];\n1084:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1085:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1086:             }\n1087: \n1088:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1089:               command: 'deep/research',\n1090:               mode: 'research',\n1091:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1092:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1093:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1094:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n1095:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n1096:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n1097:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n1098:             };\n1099:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1100:             process.exit(\n1101:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1102:                 command: 'claude',\n1103:                 args,\n1104:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1105:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1106:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1107:                 executor,\n1108:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1109:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1110:                 dispatchId,\n1111:               }),\n1112:             );\n1113:             EOF\n1114:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1115:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1116:           wait_for_completion: true\n1117:           notes:\n1118:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n1119:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n1120:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n1121:         record_executor_audit:\n1122:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n1123:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1124:           field: \"executor\"\n1125:           value:\n1126:             kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n1127:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n1128:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n1129:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n1130:         if_cli_opencode:\n1131:           command: |\n1132:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1133:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1134:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1135: \n1136:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1137: \n1138:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1139:             const executor = {\n1140:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n1141:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1142:               configDir: null,\n1143:               reasoningEffort,\n1144:               serviceTier: null,\n1145:               sandboxMode: null,\n1146:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1147:               governor: null,\n1148:             };\n1149:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1150:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n1151:               + '\\n\\n'\n1152:               + promptBody;\n1153:             const args = [\n1154:               'run',\n1155:               '--model',\n1156:               executor.model,\n1157:               '--format',\n1158:               'json',\n1159:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1160:               '--pure',\n1161:               '--dir',\n1162:               '{repo_root}',\n1163:             ];\n1164:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1165:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1166:             }\n1167:             args.push(message);\n1168: \n1169:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1170:               command: 'deep/research',\n1171:               mode: 'research',\n1172:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1173:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1174:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1175:               executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n1176:               branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n1177:               sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n1178:               generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n1179:             };\n1180:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1181:             process.exit(\n1182:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1183:                 command: 'opencode',\n1184:                 args,\n1185:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1186:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1187:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1188:                 executor,\n1189:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1190:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1191:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1192:                 input: '',\n1193:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1194:                 dispatchId,\n1195:               }),\n1196:             );\n1197:             EOF\n1198:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1199:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1200:           wait_for_completion: true\n1201:           notes:\n1202:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1203:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1204:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1205:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1206:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1207:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1208:         if_cli_codex:\n1209:           command: |\n1210:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1211:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1212:             import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n1213: \n1214:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1215: \n1216:             // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n1217:             // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n1218:             // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n1219:             // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n1220:             let codexAvailable = false;\n1221:             try {\n1222:               execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n1223:               codexAvailable = true;\n1224:             } catch {}\n1225:             if (!codexAvailable) {\n1226:               console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n1227:               process.exit(1);\n1228:             }\n1229: \n1230:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1231:             const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n1232:             const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n1233:             const executor = {\n1234:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n1235:               model,\n1236:               configDir: null,\n1237:               reasoningEffort,\n1238:               serviceTier,\n1239:               sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n1240:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1241:               governor: null,\n1242:             };\n1243: \n1244:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1245: \n1246:             // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A research\n1247:             // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n1248:             // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n1249:             // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n1250:             const args = ['exec'];\n1251:             if (model) {\n1252:               args.push('--model', model);\n1253:             }\n1254:             args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n1255:             if (serviceTier) {\n1256:               args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n1257:             }\n1258:             args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n1259: \n1260:             const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n1261:             process.exit(\n1262:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1263:                 command: 'codex',\n1264:                 args,\n1265:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1266:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1267:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1268:                 executor,\n1269:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1270:                 input: promptBody,\n1271:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1272:                 dispatchId,\n1273:               }),\n1274:             );\n1275:             EOF\n1276:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1277:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1278:           wait_for_completion: true\n1279:           notes:\n1280:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1281:             - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n1282:             - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n1283:             - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n1284:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1285:           validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1286:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1287:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1288:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1289:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1290:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n1291:           route_proof:\n1292:             mode: research\n1293:             target_agent: deep-research\n1294:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1295:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n1296:           dispatchReceipt:\n1297:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1298:             dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n1299:           optional_jsonl_fields:\n1300:             logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n1301:             logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n1302:             logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n1303:             skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n1304:             slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n1305:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1306:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1307:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1308:           on_failure:\n1309:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1310:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1311:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1312:           failure_reasons_reference:\n1313:             - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n1314:             - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n1315:             - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n1316:             - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n1317:             - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n1318:             - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n1319:             - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n1320:             - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n1321:             - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n1322:             - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n1323:             - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n1324:             - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n1325:             - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n1326: \n1327:       step_run_now_restore_check:\n1328:         action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n1329:         command: |\n1330:           node <<'EOF'\n1331:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n1332: \n1333:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n1334:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n1335:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n1336:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n1337:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n1338:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n1339: \n1340:           function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n1341:             if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n1342:             const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n1343:             for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n1344:               const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n1345:               if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n1346:               if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n1347:               if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n1348:             }\n1349:             return false;\n1350:           }\n1351: \n1352:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n1353:             appendFileSync(\n1354:               stateLogPath,\n1355:               `${JSON.stringify({\n1356:                 type: \"event\",\n1357:                 event: \"run_now_restored\",\n1358:                 mode: \"research\",\n1359:                 run,\n1360:                 sentinelPath,\n1361:                 timestamp,\n1362:                 sessionId,\n1363:                 generation,\n1364:               })}\\n`,\n1365:               \"utf8\",\n1366:             );\n1367:           }\n1368:           EOF\n1369:         outputs:\n1370:           - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n1371: \n1372:       step_reduce_state:\n1373:         action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n1374:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n1375:         inputs:\n1376:           latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n1377:           newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1378:           priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1379:         outputs:\n1380:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1381:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1382:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1383:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n1384:           - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n1385:           - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n1386:         failure_modes:\n1387:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1388:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1389:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1390:           question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n1391:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1392: \n1393:       step_graph_upsert:\n1394:         action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n1395:         read:\n1396:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1397:         extract:\n1398:           - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n1399:           - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n1400:           - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n1401:           - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n1402:         if_graph_events_present:\n1403:           bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n1404:           note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n1405:         if_graph_events_missing:\n1406:           proceed: true\n1407: \n1408:       step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n1409:         action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n1410:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1411:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n1412:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1413:         idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n1414:         failure_policy:\n1415:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1416:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n1417:         outputs:\n1418:           - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1419:           - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n1420: \n1421:       step_refresh_memory_context:\n1422:         action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n1423:         mcp_tool: memory_context\n1424:         invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n1425:         timeout_seconds: 5\n1426:         use_response:\n1427:           - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n1428:         failure_policy:\n1429:           mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1430:           timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n1431:         outputs:\n1432:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n1433:           - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n1434: \n1435:       step_evaluate_results:\n1436:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1437:         verify:\n1438:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1439:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1440:           - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n1441:           - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n1442:         extract:\n1443:           - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1444:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1445:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1446:           - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1447:         on_missing_outputs:\n1448:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1449:           # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n1450:           # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n1451:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n1452: \n1453:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n1454:         action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n1455:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n1456:         command: |\n1457:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1458:           import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1459: \n1460:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n1461:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n1462: \n1463:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n1464:           const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n1465:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n1466:           const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n1467:           const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n1468:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n1469: \n1470:           function readRecords(path) {\n1471:             if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n1472:             return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n1473:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1474:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1475:               .filter(Boolean)\n1476:               .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n1477:           }\n1478: \n1479:           function elapsedSince(value) {\n1480:             const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n1481:             const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n1482:             if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n1483:             return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n1484:           }\n1485: \n1486:           const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n1487:           const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n1488:           const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n1489:           const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n1490:             ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n1491:             ?? timestamp;\n1492:           const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n1493:           const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n1494:           const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n1495:           const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n1496:           const row = {\n1497:             event: 'progress',\n1498:             label: 'single',\n1499:             at: timestamp,\n1500:             duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n1501:             loop_type: 'research',\n1502:             sessionId,\n1503:             generation,\n1504:             run,\n1505:             status,\n1506:             gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n1507:           };\n1508: \n1509:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n1510:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n1511:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n1512:           });\n1513:           if (appended) {\n1514:             try {\n1515:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n1516:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n1517:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n1518:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n1519:                 event: row.event,\n1520:                 status,\n1521:               });\n1522:             } catch {}\n1523:           }\n1524:           EOF\n1525:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1526:         outputs:\n1527:           - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n1528: \n1529:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1530:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n1531:         read:\n1532:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1533:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1534:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 700-1534. Use offset=1535 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          branch_on: \"convergence_mode == 'divergent' AND reason is in ['composite_converged', 'all_questions_answered']\"\n          if_divergent_eligible:\n            eligibility_contract:\n              required_decision: \"STOP\"\n              eligible_reasons: [composite_converged, all_questions_answered]\n              excluded_reasons: [maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, minIterationsNotReached, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n              fail_closed: \"Any missing or ambiguous reason uses if_existing_terminal_path without preparing a pivot.\"\n            steps:\n              step_prepare_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Generate state-grounded research candidates and prepare or resume the pivot transaction\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import {\n                    buildResearchPivotPreparationInput,\n                    renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/divergent-research-pivot.ts';\n                  import {\n                    preparePivotTransaction,\n                  } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n\n                  const input = buildResearchPivotPreparationInput({\n                    artifactRoot: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n                    configPath: '{state_paths.config}',\n                    stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                    strategyPath: '{state_paths.strategy}',\n                    registryPath: '{state_paths.registry}',\n                    currentIteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                    maxIterations: Number('{max_iterations}'),\n                    triggerReason: '{reason}',\n                  });\n                  const prepared = await preparePivotTransaction(input);\n                  const seatPrompts = prepared.status === 'pending'\n                    ? Object.fromEntries(prepared.missingSeats.map((seat) => [\n                        seat.id,\n                        renderResearchPivotSeatPrompt(seat, prepared.dispatchContext),\n                      ]))\n                    : {};\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify({\n                    ...prepared,\n                    seatPrompts,\n                    boundaryRejections: input.boundaryRejections,\n                  })}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_prepare_json: \"The complete parsed JSON result\"\n                  - pivot_prepare_status: \"status from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_id: \"pivotId from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_paths_json: \"paths from the prepare result as JSON\"\n                  - pivot_resumed: \"resumed from the prepare result\"\n                  - pivot_missing_seat_ids: \"missingSeats ids from a pending result\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_json: \"The seat-001 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_json: \"The seat-002 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_json: \"The seat-003 mandate object from missingSeats\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-001']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-002']\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_prompt: \"seatPrompts['seat-003']\"\n                  - pivot_dispatch_context_json: \"dispatchContext from a pending result as JSON\"\n                short_circuit: \"When status is completed or failed, skip all dispatch and record steps and bind this result as pivot_result.\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the analytical research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_001_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_001.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_001_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_001:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-001 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-001'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_001_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_001_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_001_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_001_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_001_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_001_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the critical research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_002_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_002.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_002_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_002:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-002 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-002'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_002_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_002_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_002_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_002_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_002_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_002_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Natively dispatch the pragmatic research direction-selection seat\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                capture_timing: true\n                if_native:\n                  dispatch:\n                    agent: deep-research\n                    model: opus\n                    context_source: \"pivot_seat_003_prompt\"\n                  wait_for_completion: true\n                failure_contract: \"A native dispatch failure binds status=rejected, a {name,message} error, and the measured timestamps/duration, then proceeds to step_record_pivot_seat_003.\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status: \"fulfilled or rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_output_json: \"Raw native return serialized as JSON when fulfilled\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_error_json: \"{name,message} when rejected\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso: \"Dispatch start timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso: \"Dispatch completion timestamp\"\n                  - pivot_seat_003_duration_ms: \"Dispatch duration in milliseconds\"\n\n              step_record_pivot_seat_003:\n                action: \"Durably record the seat-003 native dispatch outcome\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending' or pivot_missing_seat_ids does not contain 'seat-003'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { recordPivotSeatResult } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  const status = '{pivot_seat_003_dispatch_status}';\n                  const outcome = status === 'fulfilled'\n                    ? { status, output: {pivot_seat_003_output_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') }\n                    : { status: 'rejected', error: {pivot_seat_003_error_json}, startedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_started_at_iso}', completedAtIso: '{pivot_seat_003_completed_at_iso}', durationMs: Number('{pivot_seat_003_duration_ms}') };\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(recordPivotSeatResult({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', seat: {pivot_seat_003_json}, outcome }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n\n              step_finalize_divergent_pivot:\n                action: \"Finalize the prepared pivot after all missing native seats are durable\"\n                skip_when: \"pivot_prepare_status != 'pending'\"\n                command: |\n                  node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n                  import { finalizePivotTransaction } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/divergent-pivot.ts';\n                  process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(finalizePivotTransaction({ paths: {pivot_paths_json}, pivotId: '{pivot_id}', resumed: {pivot_resumed} }))}\\n`);\n                  EOF\n                working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n                outputs:\n                  - pivot_finalize_json: \"The complete parsed final result\"\n\n              step_resolve_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Use prepare's terminal result on resume/short-circuit, otherwise use finalize's result\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_prepare_status\"\n                if_pending: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_finalize_json}\" } }\n                if_completed_or_failed: { bind: { pivot_result: \"{pivot_prepare_json}\" } }\n\n              step_apply_divergent_pivot_result:\n                action: \"Adopt a successful focus or fail closed to the existing synthesis path\"\n                branch_on: \"pivot_result.status\"\n                if_completed:\n                  set:\n                    next_focus: \"{pivot_result.restoredFocus}\"\n                    pivot_lineage: \"Pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} selected {pivot_result.selectedCandidate.id} from source iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                    saturated_directions: \"{pivot_result.completedEvent.saturatedDirections}\"\n                  command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n                  log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} restored focus to {pivot_result.restoredFocus}; continuing iteration {current_iteration}.\"\n                  proceed_to: step_rejected_pattern_cache\n                if_failed:\n                  log: \"Divergent pivot {pivot_result.pivotId} failed closed ({pivot_result.failureReason}); proceeding to synthesis.\"\n                  skip_to: phase_synthesis\n            on_error:\n              log: \"Divergent pivot integration error; failing closed to the existing synthesis path.\"\n              skip_to: phase_synthesis\n          if_existing_terminal_path:\n            log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n            skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n        action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        candidate_sources:\n          next_focus:\n            category: \"next-focus\"\n            values:\n              - \"{next_focus}\"\n              - \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              - \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n          recovery:\n            category: \"recovery\"\n            values:\n              - \"{recovery_strategy}\"\n              - \"{least_explored}\"\n          ideas:\n            category: \"ideas\"\n            values:\n              - \"{promoted_ideas_list}\"\n            optional_file: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\"\n        algorithm: |\n          Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\n          reducer pass as the source of truth.\n          Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\n          rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\n          are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\n          selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\n          halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\n        outputs:\n          - accepted_next_focus: \"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_recovery_candidate: \"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed ideas candidate, or null\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Suppressed candidate diagnostics from registry.suppressedCandidates plus any current-step matches\"\n        if_next_focus_suppressed:\n          set: { next_focus: \"{accepted_next_focus || accepted_recovery_candidate || accepted_idea_candidate}\" }\n          log: \"Rejected-pattern cache suppressed the prior candidate; dispatching the next accepted candidate.\"\n        if_all_candidates_suppressed:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"All next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates match active rejected patterns. Remove/reset the rejected pattern or provide a new focus.\"\n\n      step_ideas_backlog_lifecycle:\n        action: \"Track reducer-owned observed/promoted/rejected idea lifecycle before dispatch\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        lifecycle:\n          observed_event: \"idea_observed\"\n          promoted_event: \"idea_promoted\"\n          rejected_event: \"idea_rejected\"\n          min_observations: \"{min_idea_observations}\"\n          authority: \"Leaf agents emit observations only; reducer emits promotions and owns ranking.\"\n        validate:\n          - \"If new leaf-authored output includes idea_promoted, fail validation; only reducer output may append idea_promoted.\"\n          - \"If promoted_ideas_count > 0 and next_focus is empty or all questions are resolved, prefer the first unsuppressed promoted idea.\"\n          - \"If suppressed_ideas_count > 0, do not render those ideas into dispatch context.\"\n        outputs:\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived observed ideas count\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived promoted ideas count after minIdeaObservations\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Reducer-derived rejected/suppressed ideas count\"\n          - accepted_idea_candidate: \"First unsuppressed promoted idea, or null\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            {memory_context_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              carried_forward_open_questions: \"{carried_forward_open_questions}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n              saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.type}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/research',\n              mode: 'research',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.type}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.type}',\n              sessionId: '{config.lineage.sessionId}',\n              generation: Number('{config.lineage.generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n            // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n            // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n            // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n            let codexAvailable = false;\n            try {\n              execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n              codexAvailable = true;\n            } catch {}\n            if (!codexAvailable) {\n              console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n              process.exit(1);\n            }\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n            const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model,\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier,\n              sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n\n            // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A research\n            // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n            // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n            // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n            const args = ['exec'];\n            if (model) {\n              args.push('--model', model);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n            if (serviceTier) {\n              args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n\n            const dispatchId = 'research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: promptBody,\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n            - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n            - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type research --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, newInfoRatio, status, focus, mode]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: research\n            target_agent: deep-research\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"research-i{current_iteration}-g{config.lineage.generation}\"\n          optional_jsonl_fields:\n            logOffset: \"Byte offset where the seekable log region starts\"\n            logSize: \"Byte length of the seekable log region\"\n            logPath: \"Absolute path to the file containing the seekable log region\"\n            skippedCount: \"Missed fixed-rate slots counted for the completed dispatch; 0 when no slot was missed\"\n            slotDurationMs: \"Monotonic elapsed duration for the completed dispatch slot\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n          failure_reasons_reference:\n            - \"iteration_file_missing — iteration narrative markdown not written\"\n            - \"iteration_file_empty — iteration narrative markdown is zero bytes\"\n            - \"jsonl_not_appended — state log file did not grow since pre-dispatch snapshot\"\n            - \"jsonl_missing_fields — last state-log record omits required schema fields\"\n            - \"jsonl_parse_error — last state-log line is not valid JSON\"\n            - \"jsonl_wrong_type — last state-log record uses type!='iteration' (e.g. 'iteration_delta'); reducer will silently drop\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing — per-iteration deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl not written\"\n            - \"delta_file_empty — per-iteration delta file exists but has zero bytes\"\n            - \"delta_file_missing_iteration_record — delta file lacks any record with type='iteration'\"\n            - \"route_proof_missing — state-log or delta iteration record omits route-proof fields\"\n            - \"route_proof_mismatch — state-log or delta iteration record does not match the resolved deep route\"\n            - \"executor_missing — non-native executor did not record provenance\"\n            - \"dispatch_failure_logged — last record is an explicit dispatch_failure event\"\n\n      step_run_now_restore_check:\n        action: \"Record a run-now sentinel recreated during the completed dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function hasAcceptedCurrentRun() {\n            if (!existsSync(stateLogPath)) return false;\n            const lines = readFileSync(stateLogPath, \"utf8\").trim().split(/\\r?\\n/).filter(Boolean);\n            for (let index = lines.length - 1; index >= 0; index -= 1) {\n              const record = JSON.parse(lines[index]);\n              if (record.run !== run || record.sessionId !== sessionId) continue;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_accepted\") return true;\n              if (record.event === \"run_now_rejected\") return false;\n            }\n            return false;\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath) && hasAcceptedCurrentRun()) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                event: \"run_now_restored\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                sentinelPath,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_restored: \"Emitted when an operator recreates the sentinel before the accepted dispatch completes\"\n\n      step_reduce_state:\n        action: \"Run the reducer to synchronize registry, dashboard, and strategy\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n        inputs:\n          latestJSONLDelta: \"Latest JSONL records written since the previous iteration\"\n          newIterationFile: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          priorReducedState: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n        outputs:\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} question_conflict events when inbox text disagrees with registry-owned question text\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log} idempotent idea_promoted events when observed ideas reach minIdeaObservations\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry} observedIdeas, promotedIdeas, suppressedIdeas, rejectedPatterns, and suppressedCandidates from idea lifecycle events\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n          question_conflict: \"keep registry value + append question_conflict event with inboxValue, registryValue, and operatorDecision\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Persist the latest iteration graph delta after the reducer refresh and after the iteration file exists\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n        extract:\n          - latest_graph_events: \"Read graphEvents from the latest iteration record, else []\"\n          - graph_upsert_nodes_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'node' to node payloads with label -> name and preserve remaining node fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_edges_json: \"Map latest_graph_events where type == 'edge' to edge payloads with source -> sourceId, target -> targetId, relation -> uppercase(relation), and preserve remaining edge fields\"\n          - graph_upsert_event_count: \"Count mapped node and edge events\"\n        if_graph_events_present:\n          bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"research\\\" --session-id \\\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\\\" --nodes '{graph_upsert_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_upsert_edges_json}'\"\n          note: \"Skip silently when graphEvents is missing or empty.\"\n        if_graph_events_missing:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_memory_upsert_iteration:\n        action: \"Upsert the canonical iteration evidence into Spec Kit Memory after reducer and graph persistence\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\" })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        idempotency: \"Re-running the same iteration file is safe because the memory backend upserts by path/content.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_upsert_iteration_file: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - memory_upsert_status: \"upserted | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_refresh_memory_context:\n        action: \"Refresh focused Spec Kit Memory context before the next prompt render\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_context\n        invocation: 'memory_context({ input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true })'\n        timeout_seconds: 5\n        use_response:\n          - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n        failure_policy:\n          mcp_error: \"non-fatal; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n          timeout: \"non-fatal after timeout_seconds; log advisory warning and continue with the previous memory_context_prompt_line\"\n        outputs:\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"Fresh focused context summary for the next iteration prompt\"\n          - memory_context_refresh_status: \"refreshed | advisory_error\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Reducer refreshed strategy machine-owned sections\"\n          - registry_updated: \"Reducer refreshed findings-registry.json\"\n        extract:\n          - newInfoRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - latest_focus: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include mode, sessionId, generation, durationMs, keyQuestions, answeredQuestions\n          # so the reducer can persist the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"research\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_focus}\",\"findingsCount\":0,\"newInfoRatio\":0.0,\"keyQuestions\":[],\"answeredQuestions\":[],\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_progress:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop progress row when iteration state changes\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { existsSync, readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const stateLogPath = '{state_paths.state_log}';\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = '{config.lineage.sessionId}';\n          const generation = Number('{config.lineage.generation}');\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n\n          function readRecords(path) {\n            if (!existsSync(path)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(path, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .map((line) => JSON.parse(line));\n          }\n\n          function elapsedSince(value) {\n            const startedAtMs = Date.parse(String(value ?? ''));\n            const nowMs = Date.parse(timestamp);\n            if (!Number.isFinite(startedAtMs) || !Number.isFinite(nowMs)) return 0;\n            return Math.max(0, nowMs - startedAtMs);\n          }\n\n          const records = readRecords(stateLogPath);\n          const iterations = records.filter((record) => record.type === 'iteration');\n          const latest = iterations.at(-1) ?? {};\n          const startedAt = records.find((record) => typeof record.createdAt === 'string')?.createdAt\n            ?? records.find((record) => typeof record.timestamp === 'string')?.timestamp\n            ?? timestamp;\n          const elapsedMs = elapsedSince(startedAt);\n          const score = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.newInfoRatio)) ? Number(latest.newInfoRatio) : 0;\n          const run = Number.isFinite(Number(latest.run)) ? Number(latest.run) : Number('{current_iteration}');\n          const status = typeof latest.status === 'string' ? latest.status : 'unknown';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'progress',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: elapsedMs,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            run,\n            status,\n            gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, elapsed_ms: elapsedMs, score },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run, status, gauges: { iterations: iterations.length, score } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation, run },\n                event: row.event,\n                status,\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"","lineStart":700,"lineEnd":1534,"totalLines":1535,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784444172202,"end":1784444172253}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08341c15d884b8b1016a5c750c1c588191b4ee4c46ff182be9"}},"id":"prt_f7929376c001e7SVp3h51ESjus","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f7929132c001D9endXAwYI5Bt4"}}
