CHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n - Directly tracing manifest construction, eligibility, lexical ranking, cards, and hydration exposed the repeated corpus-wide I/O and preserved safety invariants (iteration 1).\n - A bounded full-corpus benchmark quantified the current read-time cost at about 6.25 seconds (iteration 1).\n+- Tracing schema, mutation, scanner, vector, and hybrid-query modules as one lifecycle separated durable database invariants from rebuildable caches (iteration 2).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - The prompt's 1,291-style count could not be reconciled with three current repository surfaces, which consistently report 1,290 (iteration 1).\n+- The requested `mcp_server/database/` path contains runtime artifacts rather than schema source; ownership had to be followed into canonical `mcp-server/lib/` modules (iteration 2).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n@@ -47,18 +49,20 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n - Treating `_retrieval-manifest.json` as the indexed database: it is a denormalized snapshot that is fully rebuilt and parsed (iteration 1).\n - Treating slug/path as canonical identity: UUID is primary and slug is a separate unique locator (iteration 1).\n+- Reusing `memory_index` directly: its cognition, governance, chunking, and retention fields are domain-specific (iteration 2).\n+- Making mtime or vector availability authoritative for retrieval: hashes and lexical fallback are required (iteration 2).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n-All five key questions remain open. Q4's current-state half is mapped; target retrieval and migration integration remain unresolved.\n+All five key questions remain open. Q2 and Q3 now have reusable persistence contracts but need a concrete style schema and multi-artifact hash definition.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Map the system-spec-kit SQLite, FTS, embedding, and incremental-ingestion lifecycle end to end, then identify reusable contracts and style-specific mismatches.\n+Define and pressure-test the normalized style schema, constraints, indexes, retrieval document, and canonical aggregate hash against the current manifest fields and artifacts.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@ -12,24 +12,33 @@\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Style identity is UUID-first while slug remains a separately unique filesystem locator.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:295-315\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:483-500\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The retrieval manifest is a strict denormalized projection with provenance, facets, section pointers, and artifact hashes.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-79\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:434-513\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F4\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Every