{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784445518223,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ZLcIlYLBd7s5nwzkgrj5LrZK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n-- [ ] Q2: What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\n+- [x] Q2: What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\n@@\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n-None yet.\n+- Q2: Use normalized style/provenance/crawl/artifact/term/token/section tables keyed by stable style identity; keep retrieval documents, trigger-maintained FTS5, and profile-addressed vectors as derived projections, with separate aggregate and retrieval hashes (iteration 3).\n@@\n - Tracing schema, mutation, scanner, vector, and hybrid-query modules as one lifecycle separated durable database invariants from rebuildable caches (iteration 2).\n+- Mapping every manifest field into normalized destinations and running an in-memory SQLite pressure test validated uniqueness, tombstone, FTS-trigger, and index-plan constraints (iteration 3).\n@@\n - The requested `mcp_server/database/` path contains runtime artifacts rather than schema source; ownership had to be followed into canonical `mcp-server/lib/` modules (iteration 2).\n+- An initial pressure-test DDL used invalid quoting; correcting SQL literals preserved the schema and completed the test (iteration 3).\n@@\n - Making mtime or vector availability authoritative for retrieval: hashes and lexical fallback are required (iteration 2).\n+- One JSON blob per style, DESIGN-only freshness, full-artifact embeddings, and independently stored derivable counters (iteration 3).\n@@\n-All five key questions remain open. Q2 and Q3 now have reusable persistence contracts but need a concrete style schema and multi-artifact hash definition.\n+Q1, Q3, Q4, and Q5 remain open. Q2 is answered with a concrete normalized schema and dual-hash contract.\n@@\n-Define and pressure-test the normalized style schema, constraints, indexes, retrieval document, and canonical aggregate hash against the current manifest fields and artifacts.\n+Design the crash-safe incremental indexing state machine: scan hints, hash verification, parse/validate, atomic upsert, vector queue, tombstones, rebuild, rollback, and generation publication.\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"text\":\"What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\"},\n@@\n-  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"text\":\"What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Normalized style-owned source tables plus derived retrieval, FTS, and vector projections with dual freshness hashes.\"}\n+  ],\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"I002-F7\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Begin with hard eligibility filters plus attributed FTS/vector fusion and defer memory-specific ranking lanes.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1593-1676\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1776-1929\"]}\n+    {\"id\":\"I002-F7\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Begin with hard eligibility filters plus attributed FTS/vector fusion and defer memory-specific ranking lanes.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1593-1676\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1776-1929\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F1\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Use normalized relational source state with retrieval documents, FTS, and vectors as derived projections.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts:3839-3958\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:36-73\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F2\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Map every manifest field to scalar state, normalized children, ingestion snapshots, or derived views.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:36-73\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-27\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F3\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"All artifacts drive aggregate freshness while canonical JSON, tokens, and DESIGN.md drive semantic retrieval.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:434-481\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F4\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Separate the all-artifact aggregate hash from the retrieval-document hash.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:141-176\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Canonical retrieval bytes require versioning, fixed keys, normalization, and deterministic ordering.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:322-405\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F6\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Concrete constraints, partial indexes, and external-content FTS triggers passed an SQLite pressure test.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts:399-432\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F7\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Q2 is answered by the normalized schema and index contract.\",\"sources\":[\"iterations/iteration-003.md:6-19\"]}\n@@\n-    {\"iteration\":2,\"approach\":\"Use mtime as freshness authority\",\"reason\":\"The reference implementation verifies hashes and retry state.\"}\n+    {\"iteration\":2,\"approach\":\"Use mtime as freshness authority\",\"reason\":\"The reference implementation verifies hashes and retry state.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":3,\"approach\":\"Use one JSON blob per style\",\"reason\":\"It cannot enforce or efficiently query multi-valued facets and tokens.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":3,\"approach\":\"Embed every style artifact\",\"reason\":\"Generated CSS and raw source create duplicate/noisy semantic churn.\"}\n@@\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 2,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 5,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 0,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 13,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 3,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 4,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 1,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 20,\n@@\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:12:00Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:25:00Z\"\n }\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n-- Iterations: 2 / 10\n+- Iterations: 3 / 10\n@@\n | 2 | Spec-memory persistence and retrieval lifecycle | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n+| 3 | Normalized schema and canonical hashes | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n@@\n-- 0 / 5 answered\n+- 1 / 5 answered: Q2\n@@\n-Define and pressure-test the normalized style schema and aggregate hash contract.\n+Design the crash-safe incremental indexing and publication state machine.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -5,9 +5,9 @@\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n - [ ] Q1: Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\n-- [ ] Q2: What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\n+- [x] Q2: What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\n - [ ] Q3: How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\n - [ ] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n - [ ] Q5: Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n@@ -23,23 +23,25 @@\n - Produce an actionable schema, sync design, retrieval contract, and source-of-truth migration decision with eliminated alternatives.\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n-None yet.\n+- Q2: Use normalized style/provenance/crawl/artifact/term/token/section tables keyed by stable style identity; keep retrieval documents, trigger-maintained FTS5, and profile-addressed vectors as derived projections, with separate aggregate and retrieval hashes (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n - Directly tracing manifest construction, eligibility, lexical ranking, cards, and hydration exposed the repeated corpus-wide I/O and preserved safety invariants (iteration 1).\n - A bounded full-corpus benchmark quantified the current read-time cost at about 6.25 seconds (iteration 1).\n - Tracing schema, mutation, scanner, vector, and hybrid-query modules as one lifecycle separated durable database invariants from rebuildable caches (iteration 2).\n+- Mapping every manifest field into normalized destinations and running an in-memory SQLite pressure test validated uniqueness, tombstone, FTS-trigger, and index-plan constraints (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - The prompt's 1,291-style count could not be reconciled with three current repository surfaces, which consistently report 1,290 (iteration 1).\n - The requested `mcp_server/database/` path contains runtime artifacts rather than schema source; ownership had to be followed into canonical `mcp-server/lib/` modules (iteration 2).\n+- An initial pressure-test DDL used invalid quoting; correcting SQL literals preserved the schema and completed the test (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n@@ -51,18 +53,19 @@\n - Treating `_retrieval-manifest.json` as the indexed database: it is a denormalized snapshot that is fully rebuilt and parsed (iteration 1).\n - Treating slug/path as canonical identity: UUID is primary and slug is a separate unique locator (iteration 1).\n - Reusing `memory_index` directly: its cognition, governance, chunking, and retention fields are domain-specific (iteration 2).\n - Making mtime or vector availability authoritative for retrieval: hashes and lexical fallback are required (iteration 2).\n+- One JSON blob per style, DESIGN-only freshness, full-artifact embeddings, and independently stored derivable counters (iteration 3).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n-All five key questions remain open. Q2 and Q3 now have reusable persistence contracts but need a concrete style schema and multi-artifact hash definition.\n+Q1, Q3, Q4, and Q5 remain open. Q2 is answered with a concrete normalized schema and dual-hash contract.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Define and pressure-test the normalized style schema, constraints, indexes, retrieval document, and canonical aggregate hash against the current manifest fields and artifacts.\n+Design the crash-safe incremental indexing state machine: scan hints, hash verification, parse/validate, atomic upsert, vector queue, tombstones, rebuild, rollback, and generation publication.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,14 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n     {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"text\":\"Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\"},\n-    {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"text\":\"What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\"},\n     {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"text\":\"How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\"},\n     {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"text\":\"What semantic and structured retrieval API should styles/_engine expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\"},\n     {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"text\":\"Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\"}\n   ],\n-  \"resolvedQuestions\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"text\":\"What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Normalized style-owned source tables plus derived retrieval, FTS, and vector projections with dual freshness hashes.\"}\n+  ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The current checked-in corpus has 1,290 records, not 1,291.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-6\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Style identity is UUID-first while slug remains a separately unique filesystem locator.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:295-315\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:483-500\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F3\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The retrieval manifest is a strict denormalized projection with provenance, facets, section pointers, and artifact hashes.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:29-79\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:434-513\"]},\n@@ -19,26 +20,35 @@\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F3\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Use trigger-maintained external-content FTS5 with style-specific weighted fields.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts:399-432\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/sqlite-fts.ts:150-205\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F4\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Separate embedding status, profile, cache, and vector payload while preserving lexical-only availability.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/schema.ts:175-227\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-store.ts:806-857\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F5\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Use mtime as a hint and a canonical multi-artifact hash as freshness authority.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/storage/incremental-index.ts:283-321\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/handlers/memory-index.ts:1433-1509\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I002-F6\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Keep source, FTS, and vector metadata mutations atomic and in-memory caches rebuildable.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-mutations.ts:367-420\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-mutations.ts:739-800\"]},\n-    {\"id\":\"I002-F7\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Begin with hard eligibility filters plus attributed FTS/vector fusion and defer memory-specific ranking lanes.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1593-1676\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1776-1929\"]}\n+    {\"id\":\"I002-F7\",\"iteration\":2,\"summary\":\"Begin with hard eligibility filters plus attributed FTS/vector fusion and defer memory-specific ranking lanes.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1593-1676\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:1776-1929\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F1\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Use normalized relational source state with retrieval documents, FTS, and vectors as derived projections.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts:3839-3958\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:36-73\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F2\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Map every manifest field to scalar state, normalized children, ingestion snapshots, or derived views.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:36-73\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-27\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F3\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"All artifacts drive aggregate freshness while canonical JSON, tokens, and DESIGN.md drive semantic retrieval.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:434-481\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F4\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Separate the all-artifact aggregate hash from the retrieval-document hash.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:141-176\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F5\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Canonical retrieval bytes require versioning, fixed keys, normalization, and deterministic ordering.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:322-405\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F6\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Concrete constraints, partial indexes, and external-content FTS triggers passed an SQLite pressure test.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/vector-index-schema.ts:399-432\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I003-F7\",\"iteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Q2 is answered by the normalized schema and index contract.\",\"sources\":[\"iterations/iteration-003.md:6-19\"]}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\"iteration\":1,\"approach\":\"Use the JSON retrieval manifest as the database\",\"reason\":\"It is fully parsed and regenerated, and FTS is disposable.\"},\n     {\"iteration\