{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784446345977,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_9Se1ws28q7hjiRYwQgZ2lEu1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n-- [ ] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n+- [x] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n@@\n - Q3: Use a resumable DISCOVER -> VERIFY -> PARSE_VALIDATE -> COMMIT -> VECTOR_DRAIN -> PUBLISH state machine, transactional generation publication, quarantined absence/tombstones, staged rebuilds, and generation-pointer rollback (iteration 4).\n+- Q4: Expose a v2 API separating hard eligibility from ranking signals; pin generation/profile, fuse structured/FTS/vector ranks with weighted RRF, return channel attribution and keyset cursors, recheck hydration authorization, and preserve v1 via a legacy/shadow/persistent adapter (iteration 5).\n@@\n - Pairing current manifest invalidation with scanner, retry, transaction, and staged-reindex code exposed concrete crash boundaries and recovery rules (iteration 4).\n+- Tracing current API/tests before borrowing RRF and degraded-channel behavior preserved compatibility while avoiding memory-specific ranking complexity (iteration 5).\n@@\n - Broad lifecycle searches were noisy; narrowing by named state transition found the authoritative implementation paths (iteration 4).\n+- No source path failed; adaptive memory-specific fusion was intentionally excluded for lack of style evidence (iteration 5).\n@@\n - In-place rebuilds, one-scan hard deletes, stale vector writes without CAS, and second-transaction generation publication (iteration 4).\n+- Raw-score addition, post-retrieval eligibility, offset/unpinned pagination, authorization-bearing hydration tokens, and normal-path corpus walking after cutover (iteration 5).\n@@\n-Q1, Q4, and Q5 remain open. Q2 and Q3 are answered; Q5 has a rollback/tombstone foundation but still needs the source-of-truth migration decision.\n+Q1 and Q5 remain open. Q2-Q4 are answered; the source-of-truth and cutover decision is now the primary unresolved dependency for the technology recommendation.\n@@\n-Specify the generation-consistent structured/semantic retrieval API and compatibility adapter for eligibility, FTS/vector fusion, cards, hydration, and degraded modes.\n+Resolve source of truth and migration: dual-write/read shadowing, parity gates, cutover, rollback, repair, and eventual treatment of flat artifacts.\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"text\":\"What semantic and structured retrieval API should styles/_engine expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\"},\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"text\":\"How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Resumable hash-authoritative indexing with atomic row/generation commits, idempotent vector work, quarantined deletion, staged rebuilds, and pointer rollback.\"}\n+    {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"text\":\"How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Resumable hash-authoritative indexing with atomic row/generation commits, idempotent vector work, quarantined deletion, staged rebuilds, and pointer rollback.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"text\":\"What semantic and structured retrieval API should styles/_engine expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Generation-pinned v2 API with pre-channel eligibility, structured/FTS/vector weighted RRF, channel attribution, stable cursors, guarded hydration, and a reversible v1 adapter.\"}\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"I004-F8\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Retain prior generations so rollback is a guarded pointer reversal.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:654-763\"]}\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F8\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Retain prior generations so rollback is a guarded pointer reversal.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:654-763\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F1\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"The v2 request separates hard eligibility, structured signals, channel controls, and bounded fusion depth.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/rank-fts.mjs:18-24\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs:68-81\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F2\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Every channel joins the same-generation eligible ID set before top-k retrieval.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/eligibility.mjs:15-80\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F3\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Queries, vectors, cards, cursors, and hydration bind one published generation and profile.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:119-155\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:225-291\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F4\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Use versioned weighted RRF instead of mixing raw structured, BM25, and cosine scales.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/algorithms/rrf-fusion.ts:445-576\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F5\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Native responses expose channel health and attribution while adapters preserve legacy card shape.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs:82-95\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F6\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Use generation-bound keyset cursors over a fixed candidate fusion window.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/algorithms/rrf-fusion.ts:229-242\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F7\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Hydration tokens are locators and all rights, containment, digest, and byte checks remain authoritative.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:164-199\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:315-370\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F8\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Projection failures degrade to healthy channels plus structured SQL, never normal-path corpus walking.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:2483-2553\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F9\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"A legacy/shadow/persistent adapter isolates migration and rollback from the no-walk endpoint.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:186-205\"]}\n@@\n-    {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Hard-delete after one missing scan\",\"reason\":\"Transient filesystem state is insufficient destructive evidence.\"}\n+    {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Hard-delete after one missing scan\",\"reason\":\"Transient filesystem state is insufficient destructive evidence.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Add raw channel scores\",\"reason\":\"Structured, BM25, and cosine score scales are incomparable.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Retain corpus walking as persistent fallback\",\"reason\":\"It recreates the latency and freshness problem.\"}\n@@\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 4,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 28,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 37,\n@@\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:21:18Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:40:00Z\"\n }\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n-- Iterations: 4 / 10\n+- Iterations: 5 / 10\n@@\n | 4 | Crash-safe incremental indexing | 1.00 | 8 | complete |\n+| 5 | Generation-consistent retrieval API | 1.00 | 9 | complete |\n@@\n-- 2 / 5 answered: Q2, Q3\n+- 3 / 5 answered: Q2, Q3, Q4\n@@\n-Specify the generation-consistent structured and semantic retrieval API.\n+Resolve source of truth, migration, cutover, and rollback policy.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -7,9 +7,9 @@\n ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n - [ ] Q1: Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\n - [x] Q2: What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\n - [x] Q3: How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\n-- [ ] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n+- [x] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n - [ ] Q5: Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n ## 3. NON-GOALS\n@@ -25,8 +25,9 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n - Q2: Use normalized style/provenance/crawl/artifact/term/token/section tables keyed by stable style identity; keep retrieval documents, trigger-maintained FTS5, and profile-addressed vectors as derived projections, with separate aggregate and retrieval hashes (iteration 3).\n - Q3: Use a resumable DISCOVER -> VERIFY -> PARSE_VALIDATE -> COMMIT -> VECTOR_DRAIN -> PUBLISH state machine, transactional generation publication, quarantined absence/tombstones, staged rebuilds, and generation-pointer rollback (iteration 4).\n+- Q4: Expose a v2 API separating hard eligibility from ranking signals; pin generation/profile, fuse structured/FTS/vector ranks with weighted RRF, return channel attribution and keyset cursors, recheck hydration authorization, and preserve v1 via a legacy/shadow/persistent adapter (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n@@ -35,16 +36,18 @@\n - A bounded full-corpus benchmark quantified the current read-time cost at about 6.25 seconds (iteration 1).\n - Tracing schema, mutation, scanner, vector, and hybrid-query modules as one lifecycle separated durable database invariants from rebuildable caches (iteration 2).\n - Mapping every manifest field into normalized destinations and running an in-memory SQLite pressure test validated uniqueness, tombstone, FTS-trigger, and index-plan constraints (iteration 3).\n - Pairing current manifest invalidation with scanner, retry, transaction, and staged-reindex code exposed concrete crash boundaries and recovery rules (iteration 4).\n+- Tracing current API/tests before borrowing RRF and degraded-channel behavior preserved compatibility while avoiding memory-specific ranking complexity (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - The prompt's 1,291-style count could not be reconciled with three current repository surfaces, which consistently report 1,290 (iteration 1).\n - The requested `mcp_server/database/` path contains runtime artifacts rather than schema source; ownership had to be followed into canonical `mcp-server/lib/` modules (iteration 2).\n - An initial pressure-test DDL used invalid quoting; correcting SQL literals preserved the schema and completed the test (iteration 3).\n - Broad lifecycle searches were noisy; narrowing by named state transition found the authoritative implementation paths (iteration 4).\n+- No source path failed; adaptive memory-specific fusion was intentionally excluded for lack of style evidence (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n@@ -58,18 +61,19 @@\n - Reusing `memory_index` directly: its cognition, governance, chunking, and retention fields are domain-specific (iteration 2).\n - Making mtime or vector availability authoritative for retrieval: hashes and lexical fallback are required (iteration 2).\n - One JSON blob per style, DESIGN-only freshness, full-artifact embeddings, and independently stored derivable counters (iteration 3).\n - In-place rebuilds, one-scan hard deletes, stale vector writes without CAS, and second-transaction generation publication (iteration 4).\n+- Raw-score addition, post-retrieval eligibility, offset/unpinned pagination, authorization-bearing hydration tokens, and normal-path corpus walking after cutover (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n-Q1, Q4, and Q5 remain open. Q2 and Q3 are answered; Q5 has a rollback/tombstone foundation but still needs the source-of-truth migration decision.\n+Q1 and Q5 remain open. Q2-Q4 are answered; the source-of-truth and cutover decision is now the primary unresolved dependency for the technology recommendation.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Specify the generation-consistent structured/semantic retrieval API and compatibility adapter for eligibility, FTS/vector fusion, cards, hydration, and degraded modes.\n+Resolve source of truth and migration: dual-write/read shadowing, parity gates, cutover, rollback, repair, and eventual treatment of flat artifacts.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,13 @@\n {\n   \"openQuestions\": [\n     {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"text\":\"Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\"},\n-    {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"text\":\"What semantic and structured retrieval API should styles/_engine expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\"},\n     {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"text\":\"Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\"}\n   ],\n   \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n     {\"id\":\"Q2\",\"text\":\"What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":3,\"summary\":\"Normalized style-owned source tables plus derived retrieval, FTS, and vector projections with dual freshness hashes.\"},\n-    {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"text\":\"How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Resumable hash-authoritative indexing with atomic row/generation commits, idempotent vector work, quarantined deletion, staged rebuilds, and pointer rollback.\"}\n+    {\"id\":\"Q3\",\"text\":\"How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Resumable hash-authoritative indexing with atomic row/generation commits, idempotent vector work, quarantined deletion, staged rebuilds, and pointer rollback.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"Q4\",\"text\":\"What semantic and structured retrieval API should styles/_engine expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Generation-pinned v2 API with pre-channel eligibility, structured/FTS/vector weighted RRF, channel attribution, stable cursors, guarded hydration, and a reversible v1 adapter.\"}\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The current checked-in corpus has 1,290 records, not 1,291.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-6\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Style identity is UUID-first while slug remains a separately unique filesystem locator.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:295-315\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:483-500\"]},\n@@ -35,9 +35,18 @@\n     {\"id\":\"I004-F4\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Quarantine absence, tombstone after confirmation, and hard-delete only after retention and rebuild gates.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/handlers/memory-index.ts:296-310\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/handlers/memory-index.ts:1013-1079\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I004-F5\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Publish corpus generations atomically with changed styles and bind readers to one SQLite snapshot.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:119-173\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I004-F6\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Full rebuild uses verified staged files and atomic pointer switching while old readers finish.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:484-705\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I004-F7\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Durable transaction, queue, and staging evidence makes crash recovery deterministic.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/storage/ports/contention-policy.ts:206-233\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:764-780\"]},\n-    {\"id\":\"I004-F8\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Retain prior generations so rollback is a guarded pointer reversal.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:654-763\"]}\n+    {\"id\":\"I004-F8\",\"iteration\":4,\"summary\":\"Retain prior generations so rollback is a guarded pointer reversal.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:654-763\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F1\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"The v2 request separates hard eligibility, structured signals, channel controls, and bounded fusion depth.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/rank-fts.mjs:18-24\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs:68-81\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F2\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Every channel joins the same-generation eligible ID set before top-k retrieval.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/eligibility.mjs:15-80\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F3\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Queries, vectors, cards, cursors, and hydration bind one published generation and profile.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:119-155\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:225-291\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F4\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Use versioned weighted RRF instead of mixing raw structured, BM25, and cosine scales.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/algorithms/rrf-fusion.ts:445-576\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F5\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Native responses expose channel health and attribution while adapters preserve legacy card shape.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs:82-95\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F6\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Use generation-bound keyset cursors over a fixed candidate fusion window.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/algorithms/rrf-fusion.ts:229-242\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F7\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Hydration tokens are locators and all rights, containment, digest, and byte checks remain authoritative.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:164-199\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:315-370\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F8\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Projection failures degrade to healthy channels plus structured SQL, never normal-path corpus walking.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:2483-2553\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F9\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"A legacy/shadow/persistent adapter isolates migration and rollback from the no-walk endpoint.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:186-205\"]}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\"iteration\":1,\"approach\":\"Use the JSON retrieval manifest as the database\",\"reason\":\"It is fully parsed and regenerated, and FTS is disposable.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":1,\"approach\":\"Use slug/path as canonical identity\",\"reason\":\"Current code prefers UUID and separately validates slug uniqueness.\"},\n@@ -45,20 +54,22 @@\n     {\"iteration\":2,\"approach\":\"Use mtime as freshness authority\",\"reason\":\"The reference implementation verifies hashes and retry state.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":3,\"approach\":\"Use one JSON blob per style\",\"reason\":\"It cannot enforce or efficiently query multi-valued facets and tokens.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":3,\"approach\":\"Embed every style artifact\",\"reason\":\"Generated CSS and raw source create duplicate/noisy semantic churn.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Rebuild active files in place\",\"reason\":\"Crashes and inode-bound connections can expose or retain partial state.\"},\n-    {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Hard-delete after one missing scan\",\"reason\":\"Transient filesystem state is insufficient destructive evidence.\"}\n+    {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Hard-delete after one missing scan\",\"reason\":\"Transient filesystem state is insufficient destructive evidence.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Add raw channel scores\",\"reason\":\"Structured, BM25, and cosine score scales are incomparable.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Retain corpus walking as persistent fallback\",\"reason\":\"It recreates the latency and freshness problem.\"}\n   ],\n   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 4,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 28,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 37,\n     \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n   },\n   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-1784444104016-7oed3t\",\n   \"generation\": 1,\n   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:21:18Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:40:00Z\"\n }\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -2,9 +2,9 @@\n \n ## Status\n - Lifecycle: iterating\n - Session: `fanout-sol-1784444104016-7oed3t`\n-- Iterations: 4 / 10\n+- Iterations: 5 / 10\n - Stop policy: max-iterations\n \n ## Iteration Table\n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n@@ -12,10 +12,11 @@\n | 1 | Current corpus and retrieval pipeline | 1.00 | 6 | complete |\n | 2 | Spec-memory persistence and retrieval lifecycle | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n | 3 | Normalized schema and canonical hashes | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n | 4 | Crash-safe incremental indexing | 1.00 | 8 | complete |\n+| 5 | Generation-consistent retrieval API | 1.00 | 9 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n-- 2 / 5 answered: Q2, Q3\n+- 3 / 5 answered: Q2, Q3, Q4\n \n ## Next Focus\n-Specify the generation-consistent structured and semantic retrieval API.\n+Resolve source of truth, migration, cutover, and rollback policy.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -7,9 +7,9 @@\n ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n - [ ] Q1: Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\n - [x] Q2: What schema and indexes preserve style identity, metadata, text, provenance, relationships, and embedding lifecycle?\n - [x] Q3: How should an incremental indexer detect, parse, validate, upsert, tombstone, and rebuild from the flat style folders?\n-- [ ] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n+- [x] Q4: What semantic and structured retrieval API should `styles/_engine` expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\n - [ ] Q5: Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\n <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n \n ## 3. NON-GOALS\n@@ -25,8 +25,9 @@\n <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n - Q2: Use normalized style/provenance/crawl/artifact/term/token/section tables keyed by stable style identity; keep retrieval documents, trigger-maintained FTS5, and profile-addressed vectors as derived projections, with separate aggregate and retrieval hashes (iteration 3).\n - Q3: Use a resumable DISCOVER -> VERIFY -> PARSE_VALIDATE -> COMMIT -> VECTOR_DRAIN -> PUBLISH state machine, transactional generation publication, quarantined absence/tombstones, staged rebuilds, and generation-pointer rollback (iteration 4).\n+- Q4: Expose a v2 API separating hard eligibility from ranking signals; pin generation/profile, fuse structured/FTS/vector ranks with weighted RRF, return channel attribution and keyset cursors, recheck hydration authorization, and preserve v1 via a legacy/shadow/persistent adapter (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n \n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n@@ -35,16 +36,18 @@\n - A bounded full-corpus benchmark quantified the current read-time cost at about 6.25 seconds (iteration 1).\n - Tracing schema, mutation, scanner, vector, and hybrid-query modules as one lifecycle separated durable database invariants from rebuildable caches (iteration 2).\n - Mapping every manifest field into normalized destinations and running an in-memory SQLite pressure test validated uniqueness, tombstone, FTS-trigger, and index-plan constraints (iteration 3).\n - Pairing current manifest invalidation with scanner, retry, transaction, and staged-reindex code exposed concrete crash boundaries and recovery rules (iteration 4).\n+- Tracing current API/tests before borrowing RRF and degraded-channel behavior preserved compatibility while avoiding memory-specific ranking complexity (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n - The prompt's 1,291-style count could not be reconciled with three current repository surfaces, which consistently report 1,290 (iteration 1).\n - The requested `mcp_server/database/` path contains runtime artifacts rather than schema source; ownership had to be followed into canonical `mcp-server/lib/` modules (iteration 2).\n - An initial pressure-test DDL used invalid quoting; correcting SQL literals preserved the schema and completed the test (iteration 3).\n - Broad lifecycle searches were noisy; narrowing by named state transition found the authoritative implementation paths (iteration 4).\n+- No source path failed; adaptive memory-specific fusion was intentionally excluded for lack of style evidence (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n@@ -58,18 +61,19 @@\n - Reusing `memory_index` directly: its cognition, governance, chunking, and retention fields are domain-specific (iteration 2).\n - Making mtime or vector availability authoritative for retrieval: hashes and lexical fallback are required (iteration 2).\n - One JSON blob per style, DESIGN-only freshness, full-artifact embeddings, and independently stored derivable counters (iteration 3).\n - In-place rebuilds, one-scan hard deletes, stale vector writes without CAS, and second-transaction generation publication (iteration 4).\n+- Raw-score addition, post-retrieval eligibility, offset/unpinned pagination, authorization-bearing hydration tokens, and normal-path corpus walking after cutover (iteration 5).\n <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n-Q1, Q4, and Q5 remain open. Q2 and Q3 are answered; Q5 has a rollback/tombstone foundation but still needs the source-of-truth migration decision.\n+Q1 and Q5 remain open. Q2-Q4 are answered; the source-of-truth and cutover decision is now the primary unresolved dependency for the technology recommendation.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-Specify the generation-consistent structured/semantic retrieval API and compatibility adapter for eligibility, FTS/vector fusion, cards, hydration, and degraded modes.\n+Resolve source of truth and migration: dual-write/read shadowing, parity gates, cutover, rollback, repair, and eventual treatment of flat artifacts.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n \n ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n","additions":7,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@ -1,13 +1,13 @@\