mantic and structured retrieval API should styles/_engine expose, and how should existing file-walking behavior integrate during migration?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Generation-pinned v2 API with pre-channel eligibility, structured/FTS/vector weighted RRF, channel attribution, stable cursors, guarded hydration, and a reversible v1 adapter.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"text\":\"Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Flat files own content and hydration; published SQLite generations own normal retrieval after staged parity-gated migration, with adapter/pointer rollback.\"}\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F1\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"The current checked-in corpus has 1,290 records, not 1,291.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_retrieval-manifest.json:1-6\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_manifest.json:1-10\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I001-F2\",\"iteration\":1,\"summary\":\"Style identity is UUID-first while slug remains a separately unique filesystem locator.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:295-315\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:483-500\"]},\n@@ -44,9 +44,17 @@\n     {\"id\":\"I005-F5\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Native responses expose channel health and attribution while adapters preserve legacy card shape.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/cards.mjs:82-95\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I005-F6\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Use generation-bound keyset cursors over a fixed candidate fusion window.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/algorithms/rrf-fusion.ts:229-242\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I005-F7\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Hydration tokens are locators and all rights, containment, digest, and byte checks remain authoritative.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:164-199\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:315-370\"]},\n     {\"id\":\"I005-F8\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"Projection failures degrade to healthy channels plus structured SQL, never normal-path corpus walking.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/search/hybrid-search.ts:2483-2553\"]},\n-    {\"id\":\"I005-F9\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"A legacy/shadow/persistent adapter isolates migration and rollback from the no-walk endpoint.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:186-205\"]}\n+    {\"id\":\"I005-F9\",\"iteration\":5,\"summary\":\"A legacy/shadow/persistent adapter isolates migration and rollback from the no-walk endpoint.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:186-205\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F1\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Flat artifacts remain content authority while published SQLite generations become sole normal-query authority.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/manifest.mjs:584-712\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:225-370\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F2\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Migrate through immutable baseline, staged bootstrap, shadow dual reads, canary, query cutover, then scanner retirement.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/style-library.mjs:119-155\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F3\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Separate exact compatibility parity from native-v2 relevance and operational metrics.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:225-370\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F4\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Cutover requires source-bound parity reports, health/latency gates, and rebuild/restore/rollback drills.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:615-704\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F5\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Rollback reverses adapters or generation pointers and never exports derived rows over files.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/embedders/reindex.ts:586-704\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F6\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Bounded repair differs from staged rebuild; restored checkpoints must reconcile newer source files.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/lib/storage/checkpoints.ts:3081-3310\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F7\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Deletes originate in source files, become confirmed tombstones, then purge after retention and parity gates.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp-server/handlers/memory-bulk-delete.ts:54-273\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F8\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Operator lifecycle must expose status, bootstrap, sync, shadow, checkpoint, cutover, rollback, repair, rebuild, and tombstones.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:315-370\"]}\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\"iteration\":1,\"approach\":\"Use the JSON retrieval manifest as the database\",\"reason\":\"It is fully parsed and regenerated, and FTS is disposable.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":1,\"approach\":\"Use slug/path as canonical identity\",\"reason\":\"Current code prefers UUID and separately validates slug uniqueness.\"},\n@@ -56,20 +64,22 @@\n     {\"iteration\":3,\"approach\":\"Embed every style artifact\",\"reason\":\"Generated CSS and raw source create duplicate/noisy semantic churn.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Rebuild active files in place\",\"reason\":\"Crashes and inode-bound connections can expose or retain partial state.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":4,\"approach\":\"Hard-delete after one missing scan\",\"reason\":\"Transient filesystem state is insufficient destructive evidence.\"},\n     {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Add raw channel scores\",\"reason\":\"Structured, BM25, and cosine score scales are incomparable.\"},\n-    {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Retain corpus walking as persistent fallback\",\"reason\":\"It recreates the latency and freshness problem.\"}\n+    {\"iteration\":5,\"approach\":\"Retain corpus walking as persistent fallback\",\"reason\":\"It recreates the latency and freshness problem.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":6,\"approach\":\"Make SQLite an editable content authority\",\"reason\":\"It breaks file-backed hydration and creates an unimplemented export contract.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":6,\"approach\":\"Dual-author files and SQLite\",\"reason\":\"There is no deterministic conflict winner.\"}\n   ],\n   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 2,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 3,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 37,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 6,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 1,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 45,\n     \"convergenceScore\": 0,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {}\n   },\n   \"sessionId\": \"fanout-sol-1784444104016-7oed3t\",\n   \"generation\": 1,\n   \"status\": \"iterating\",\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:40:00Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:35:04Z\"\n }\n","additions":19,"deletions":9},{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","relativePath":".opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","type":"update","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -2,9 +2,9 @@\n \n ## Status\n - Lifecycle: iterating\n - Session: `fanout-sol-1784444104016-7oed3t`\n-- Iterations: 5 / 10\n+- Iterations: 6 / 10\n - Stop policy: max-iterations\n \n ## Iteration Table\n | Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n@@ -13,10 +13,11 @@\n | 2 | Spec-memory persistence and retrieval lifecycle | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n | 3 | Normalized schema and canonical hashes | 1.00 | 7 | complete |\n | 4 | Crash-safe incremental indexing | 1.00 | 8 | complete |\n | 5 | Generation-consistent retrieval API | 1.00 | 9 | complete |\n+| 6 | Source of truth and migration policy | 0.91 | 8 | complete |\n \n ## Question Status\n-- 3 / 5 answered: Q2, Q3, Q4\n+- 4 / 5 answered: Q2, Q3, Q4, Q5\n \n ## Next Focus\n-Resolve source of truth, migration, cutover, and rollback policy.\n+Choose the minimum production topology and evaluate graph value.\n","additions":4,"deletions":3}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\nM .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784446747211,"end":1784446747217}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01e4ba9f1ff34dad016a5c7ef696648191863f574b3aec5600"}},"id":"prt_f794ff346001QQjgj4BKk9aTsA","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","messageID":"msg_f794fe05a001cRFMNd1pn3TFJ4"}}
