{"type":"text","timestamp":1784447130468,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"id":"prt_f79565ae2001tPZJuFAv1bTs78","messageID":"msg_f795645650017pigVEhMInqNSo","sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","type":"text","text":"All five architecture questions are now evidence-backed. The remaining three forced-depth iterations will not restate the recommendation; they will challenge it from operational, retrieval-quality, and implementation-sequencing angles before synthesis.","time":{"start":1784447130338,"end":1784447130465},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07724224acdb3f59016a5c809a3b188191aee25838dc36c118","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784447166134,"sessionID":"ses_086d7cfc0ffe217XO92sKCjWRm","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_aqEJleI9vigAS4q3rF470Sza","state":{"status":"error","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@\n-- [ ] Q1: Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\n+- [x] Q1: Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\n@@\n ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n+- Q1: Ship one published SQLite generation with normalized edges and FTS5 plus a profile-addressed vector projection. A dedicated graph store is unjustified until measured multi-hop workload, relevance, identity-quality, SLO, and operational gates pass (iteration 7).\n@@\n - Separating content and runtime-query authority resolved the false single-store choice while retaining no-walk retrieval and file-byte hydration guarantees (iteration 6).\n+- Reading graph storage and query modules together, then measuring actual relationship resolution, distinguished graph-shaped data from a graph-engine requirement (iteration 7).\n@@\n - A single-store authority framing could not satisfy both query and hydration guarantees; plane-specific authority was required (iteration 6).\n+- Broad `similar` searches were noisy; a bounded parser was needed to quantify target resolution and topology readiness (iteration 7).\n@@\n - Editable SQLite content authority, dual-write content authority, permanent dual reads, DB-only deletion, and blind checkpoint restoration (iteration 6).\n+- Dedicated graph launch topology, unresolved labels as canonical edges, materialized derived similarities, and transitive similarity expansion (iteration 7).\n@@\n-Only Q1 remains open. Q2-Q5 define schema, sync, API, and source-of-truth migration; iterations 7-10 must pressure-test topology, graph value, operations, and final coherence.\n+All five key questions are answered. Iterations 8-10 are forced-depth adversarial passes for operational SLOs, retrieval quality/evaluation, and implementation sequencing.\n@@\n-Choose the minimum production topology and quantify whether a graph store adds enough retrieval or operational value beyond SQLite, FTS5, vectors, and relational edges.\n+Pressure-test the recommended topology against concurrency, file placement, cold starts, corruption boundaries, backup/recovery size, and measurable SLOs.\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/findings-registry.json\n@@\n-  \"openQuestions\": [\n-    {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"text\":\"Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\"}\n-  ],\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"text\":\"Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Flat files own content and hydration; published SQLite generations own normal retrieval after staged parity-gated migration, with adapter/pointer rollback.\"}\n+    {\"id\":\"Q5\",\"text\":\"Should flat files or the database be the source of truth, and what migration, rollback, and verification stages minimize risk?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Flat files own content and hydration; published SQLite generations own normal retrieval after staged parity-gated migration, with adapter/pointer rollback.\"},\n+    {\"id\":\"Q1\",\"text\":\"Which storage architecture best fits style retrieval: SQLite plus embeddings, graph, or a hybrid?\",\"resolvedAtIteration\":7,\"summary\":\"SQLite with FTS5, normalized edges, and profile-addressed vectors; no dedicated graph until workload, relevance, identity, SLO, and operational gates justify one.\"}\n@@\n-    {\"id\":\"I006-F8\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Operator lifecycle must expose status, bootstrap, sync, shadow, checkpoint, cutover, rollback, repair, rebuild, and tombstones.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:315-370\"]}\n+    {\"id\":\"I006-F8\",\"iteration\":6,\"summary\":\"Operator lifecycle must expose status, bootstrap, sync, shadow, checkpoint, cutover, rollback, repair, rebuild, and tombstones.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/_engine/hydrate.mjs:315-370\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F1\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Canonical styles contain explained similar-business candidates omitted from the current projection.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/shade/shade-canonical.json:102-118\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F2\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Only 2,269 of 5,812 similar labels uniquely resolve; unresolved targets must be quarantined.\",\"sources\":[\"iterations/iteration-007.md:7-8\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F3\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Both named graph databases are SQLite adjacency projections with indexed endpoints and transactions.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/council/council-graph-db.ts:119-176\",\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:234-298\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F4\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Named graph queries are mostly one-hop SQL with bounded application BFS for exceptional paths.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/council/council-graph-query.ts:191-227\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F5\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Current style relationships need direct neighbors, shared joins, and vector neighbors, not transitive graph semantics.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/shade/shade-canonical.json:102-118\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F6\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Minimum topology is SQLite, FTS5, normalized edges, and a profile-addressed vector projection.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:252-298\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F7\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Any future graph remains a rebuildable generation-stamped projection with graph-down fallback.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/council/council-graph-db.ts:3-4\"]},\n+    {\"id\":\"I007-F8\",\"iteration\":7,\"summary\":\"Graph promotion requires measured traversal demand, SLO failure, relevance lift, identity readiness, and operability.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-query.ts:644-805\"]}\n@@\n-    {\"iteration\":6,\"approach\":\"Dual-author files and SQLite\",\"reason\":\"There is no deterministic conflict winner.\"}\n+    {\"iteration\":6,\"approach\":\"Dual-author files and SQLite\",\"reason\":\"There is no deterministic conflict winner.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":7,\"approach\":\"Launch with a dedicated graph database\",\"reason\":\"No current workload needs native variable-depth traversal and relationship identity is immature.\"},\n+    {\"iteration\":7,\"approach\":\"Treat similarity as transitive\",\"reason\":\"The source relationship semantics do not justify transitive relevance.\"}\n@@\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 6,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 1,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 45,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 7,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 53,\n@@\n-  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:35:04Z\"\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-19T07:42:08Z\"\n }\n*** Update File: .opencode/specs/sk-design/012-style-database-and-interface-commands/001-research-style-database/research/lineages/sol/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@\n-- Iterations: 6 / 10\n+- Iterations: 7 / 10\n@@\n | 6 | Source of truth and migration policy | 0.91 | 8 | complete |\n+| 7 | Minimum topology and graph boundary | 1.00 | 8 | complete |\n@@\n-- 4 / 5 answere